eators%2C%20not%20destroyers.%20Slightly%20under%20half%20of%20the%20companies%20surveyed%20believe%20AI%20technologies%20will%20lead%20to%20new%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-jobs-people-are-fine-microsoft-2023-5%5C%22%3EA%20separate%20survey%20by%20Microsoft%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-jobs-people-are-fine-microsoft-2023-5%5C%22%3Epublished%20in%20May%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20the%20majority%20of%20workers%20are%20pretty%20comfortable%20with%20AI%20taking%20over%20parts%20of%20their%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20those%20pesky%2C%20repetitive%20tasks%20that%20can%20be%20delegated%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they're%20not%20ok%20with%20total%20replacement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20to%20be%20sure%2C%20around%2025%25%20of%20HSBC's%20respondents%20believed%20AI%20would%20cost%20humans%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20and%20some%20workers%20are%20already%20falling%20into%20the%20minority%20group%20of%20being%20replaced%20by%20the%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20nearly%204%2C000%20people%20in%20the%20US%20were%20laid%20off%20because%20of%20AI%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-lost-in-may-because-of-ai-report-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInsider%20reported%2C%20citing%20data%20from%20a%20human%20resources%20firm's%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20one%20e-commerce%20CEO%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-chatbot-ceo-laid-off-staff-human-support-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaid%20off%2090%25%20of%20its%20customer%20support%20staff%20after%20an%20AI%20chatbot%20outperformed%20them%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20Insider%20reported%20in%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20the%20AI%20debate%20rages%20on%2C%20perhaps%20we're%20missing%20one%20crucial%20point%3A%20Rather%20than%20obsessing%20over%20AI%20costing%20jobs%2C%20we%20should%20b