s-breach-us-ambassadors-emails%2Famp_articleshow%2F102001767.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Just%20Before%20Independence%2C%20Travancore%20Too%20Declared%20it%20Would%20Not%20Be%20a%20Part%20of%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21084954%2FBhaktivilas.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ESituated%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20southwest%20coast%2C%20Travancore%20had%20access%20to%20the%20main%20trade%20routes%20crossing%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%2C%20putting%20it%2C%20as%20the%20India%20Office%20conceded%2C%20in%20a%20position%20%E2%80%98to%20assert%20effective%20independence%E2%80%99.%20Its%20population%20of%2060%20lakh%20in%201947%20had%20a%20literacy%20rate%20of%2047%20per%20cent%20%E2%80%93%20three%20times%20higher%20than%20the%20rest%20of%20British%20India.%20It%20was%20also%20progressive.%20In%201936%2C%20it%20became%20the%20first%20state%20to%20open%20its%20temples%20to%20Untouchables%2C%20though%20the%20reasons%20for%20its%20doing%20so%20were%20largely%20pragmatic.%20Thousands%20of%20Untouchables%20were%20converting%20to%20Christianity%20and%20becoming%20politically%20active.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20288px)%2085vw%2C%20288px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21084212%2FDethroned.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22288%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21084212%2FDethroned.jpeg%20798w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21084212%2FDethroned-200x300.jpeg%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21084212%2FDethroned-681x1024.jpeg%20681w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-664298%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22433%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EJohn%20Zubrzycki%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EDethroned%3A%20Patel%2C%20Menon%20and%20the%20Integration%20of%20Princely%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EJuggernaut%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETravancore%20was%20verdant%20and%20resource%20rich%2C%20with%20forests%20of%20teak%2C%20ebony%20and%20sandalwood.%20It%20produced%20tea%20and%20spices%2C%20rubber%2C%20coconut%20and%20coir%20products%2C%20and%20also%20had%20mineral%20deposits%2C%20including%20graphite%2C%20mica%20and%20kaolin.%20Most%20importantly%2C%20Travancore%20had%20the%20second%20largest%20known%20deposits%20of%20monazite%20in%20the%20world.%20The%20strategic%20value%20of%20the%20rare%20earth%20had%20soared%20after%20the%20US%20dropped%20two%20atomic%20bombs%20on%20Hiroshima%20and%20Nagasaki%20in%20August%201945.%20A%20by-product%20of%20monazite%20was%20thorium%2C%20a%20crucial%20ingredient%20in%20the%20operation%20of%20nuclear%20reactors%20and%20in%20the%20manufacture%20of%20nuclear%20weapons.%20C.P.%20Ramaswami%20Aiyar%E2%80%99s%2011%20June%20declaration%20that%20his%20state%20would%20become%20independent%20once%20power%20was%20transferred%20had%20rattled%20Mountbatten%2C%20Nehru%20and%20the%20Congress%20leadership.%20In%20a%20press%20conference%20a%20few%20days%20later%2C%20the%20dewan%20cited%20the%20defeat%20of%20a%20Dutch%20naval%20fleet%20in%201741%20as%20proof%20of%20Travancore%E2%80%99s%20former%20glory.%20As%20an%20independent%20nation%2C%20his%20state%20would%20be%20in%20%E2%80%98no%20worse%20position%20than%20Denmark%2C%20Switzerland%20and%20Siam%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20additional%20reason%20to%20not%20accede%20was%20India%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20open%20diplomatic%20relations%20with%20the%20Soviet%20Union.%20This%2C%20in%20Aiyar%E2%80%99s%20view%2C%20would%20lead%20to%20the%20establishment%20of%20Russian%20embassies%20and%20consulates%20all%20over%20India%2C%20affording%20%E2%80%98immense%20facilities%20for%20infiltration%20of%20Communist%20propaganda%2C%20money%20and%20violent%20activities%20which%20have%20already%20been%20notorious%20in%20Cochin%20and%20British%20Malabar%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20insisted%20his%20position%20was%20final%20and%20there%20could%20be%20no%20negotiations%20as%20the%20state%20was%20ruled%20%E2%80%98in%20the%20name%20and%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20tutelary%20deity%2C%20Sri%20Padmanabha%E2%80%99.%20Born%20the%20son%20of%20a%20Brahmin%20lawyer%20in%201879%2C%20Aiyar%20followed%20the%20same%20path%20as%20his%20father%2C%20graduating%20with%20distinction%20from%20the%20Law%20School%20in%20Madras%20and%20joining%20the%20Madras%20High%20Court%20Bar%20in%201903.%20He%20went%20on%20to%20become%20the%20advocate%20general%20in%20Madras%2C%20law%20member%20of%20the%20viceroy%E2%80%99s%20Executive%20Council%20and%20a%20representative%20of%20the%20British%20India%20delegation%20at%20the%20first%20two%20Round%20Table%20Conferences%20in%20London.%20In%201931%2C%20he%20agreed%20to%20serve%20as%20legal%20and%20constitutional%20adviser%20to%20the%20Maharaja%20of%20Travancore%20and%20then%20as%20legal%20adviser%20to%20the%20maharaja%E2%80%99s%20mother%2C%20Sethu%20Parvathi%2C%20also%20known%20as%20Junior%20Maharani.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20persistent%20rumours%20that%20he%20was%20in%20a%20relationship%20with%20her%2C%20he%20was%20elevated%20to%20the%20post%20of%20dewan%20in%201937.%20According%20to%20Clarmont%20Skrine%2C%20who%20served%20as%20the%20resident%20in%20Travancore%20in%201938%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20most%20striking%20feature%20of%20the%20situation%20is%20the%20intense%2C%20almost%20hysterical%2C%20hatred%20shown%20by%20the%20educated%20and%20semi-educated%20classes%20for%20the%20Dewan.%20With%20a%20few%20exceptions%2C%20everyone%20in%20the%20State%20seems%20to%20long%20for%20his%20removal%2C%20and%20many%20yearn%20also%20for%20his%20ruin%20and%20disgrace.%E2%80%99%20Though%20his%20aims%20were%20the%20peace%20and%20prosperity%20of%20Travancore%2C%20%E2%80%98his%20methods%20are%20Machiavellian%3B%20he%20rules%20by%20dividing%2C%20he%20bribes%20with%20office%20and%20other%20favours%2C%20he%20sets%20traps%20for%20his%20critics%20and%20plays%20on%20the%20weaknesses%20of%20his%20enemies.%20It%20is%20no%20wonder%20that%20the%20man%20in%20the%20street%20does%20not%20love%20him.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20239px)%2085vw%2C%20239px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21085115%2FCPRamaswami_Aiyar_1939.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22239%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21085115%2FCPRamaswami_Aiyar_1939.jpg%20239w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21085115%2FCPRamaswami_Aiyar_1939-205x300.jpg%20205w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-664301%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22350%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EC.P.%20Ramaswami%20Aiyar.%20Photo%3A%20Public%20domain%2C%20from%20The%20Hindu%E2%80%99s%20archives%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESkrine%E2%80%99s%20successor%20as%20resident%2C%20H.J.%20Todd%20dismissed%20Aiyar%20as%20a%20vain%20man%2C%20%E2%80%98very%20susceptible%20to%20flattery%20.%20.%20.%20Likes%20to%20be%20treated%20as%20a%20cosmopolitan%2C%20man%20of%20the%20world%20rather%20than%20as%20an%20Indian%3B%20and%20although%20he%20pays%20lip%20service%20to%20nationalism%20and%20his%20religion%20he%20voices%2C%20privately%2C%20much%20contempt%20for%20his%20politically%20minded%20compatriots%20and%20the%20superstitions%20of%20the%20ultra-devout.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20view%20that%20Wavell%20concurred%20with%2C%20noting%20in%20his%20journal%20in%201946%3A%20%E2%80%98There%20is%20no%20doubt%20that%20Travancore%20is%20a%20one-man%20show%2C%20and%20the%20one%20man%20is%20Sir%20C.P.%20There%20is%20no%20doubt%20about%20his%20efficiency%2C%20his%20charm%20when%20he%20chooses%20to%20exert%20it%2C%20or%20his%20determination%20to%20get%20his%20own%20way.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESupport%20for%20Travancore%20came%20from%20an%20unexpected%20quarter.%20In%20June%201947%2C%20Vinayak%20Damodar%20Savarkar%20wrote%20to%20Aiyar%20backing%20the%20maharaja%20and%20his%20%E2%80%98courageous%20and%20far-sighted%20determination%E2%80%99%20to%20seek%20independence.%20%E2%80%98The%20Nizam%2C%20Muslim%20Ruler%20of%20Hyderabad%2C%20has%20already%20proclaimed%20his%20independence%20and%20other%20Muslim%20states%20are%20likely%20to%20do%20so.%20Hindu%20states%20are%20bold%20enough%20to%20assert%20they%20have%20the%20same%20rights.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESavarkar%E2%80%99s%20views%20were%20not%20shared%20among%20the%20nationalist%20leaders.%20Gandhi%20blasted%20Travancore%E2%80%99s%20bid%20as%20%E2%80%98tantamount%20to%20a%20declaration%20of%20war%20on%20free%20millions%20of%20India%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENehru%20warned%20that%20the%20state%20%E2%80%98would%20be%20starved%20out%E2%80%99%20and%20that%20an%20economic%20blockade%20%E2%80%98would%20lead%20to%20the%20elimination%20of%20independence%20within%20three%20months%E2%80%99.%20Responding%20to%20what%20he%20called%20a%20%E2%80%98pistol%20at%20my%20head%E2%80%99%2C%20Aiyar%20raised%20the%20stakes%20by%20banning%20the%20Travancore%20state%20unit%20of%20the%20Congress%20party%20and%20starting%20negotiations%20for%20the%20purchase%20of%20rice%20from%20Sindh%20to%20break%20a%20possible%20embargo%20on%20foodgrains.%20Similar%20deals%20were%20being%20negotiated%20with%20Burma%20and%20Siam.%20To%20compensate%20for%20the%20closure%20of%20the%20Indian%20markets%20to%20Travancore%E2%80%99s%20exports%2C%20arrangements%20were%20made%20for%20the%20sale%20of%20copra%20and%20coconut%20oil%20products%20to%20Pakistan%20and%20Australia.%20When%20Indian%20textile%20mills%20refused%20to%20supply%20Travancore%20with%20cotton%2C%20Aiyar%20planned%20discussions%20with%20British%20and%20American%20mills.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20436px)%2085vw%2C%20436px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21084326%2FJohn-Z-high-res.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22436%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21084326%2FJohn-Z-high-res.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21084326%2FJohn-Z-high-res-300x200.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21084326%2FJohn-Z-high-res-1024x683.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-664299%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22290%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EJohn%20Zubrzycki.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClosely%20watching%20the%20developments%2C%20Jinnah%20wired%20Aiyar%20on%2020%20June%20promising%20that%20Pakistan%20was%20%E2%80%98ready%20to%20establish%20a%20relationship%20with%20Travancore%20which%20will%20be%20of%20mutual%20advantage%E2%80%99.%20Maharaja%20Rama%20Varma%20Tiruvithamkoor%20had%20already%20named%20Khan%20Bahadur%20Abdul%20Karim%20Sahib%2C%20former%20inspector%20general%20of%20police%2C%20as%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20trade%20representative%20to%20Pakistan.%20Aiyar%20responded%20by%20proposing%20that%20a%20treaty%20be%20signed%20between%20the%20%E2%80%98independent%20Sovereign%20State%E2%80%99%20of%20Travancore%20and%20the%20government%20of%20Pakistan.%20Jinnah%20followed%20up%20with%20promises%20of%20food%20aid%20if%20India%20imposed%20an%20embargo.%20Writing%20to%20Mountbatten%2C%20Aiyar%20lauded%20the%20Muslim%20League%E2%80%99s%20leader%20as%20%E2%80%98a%20realist%E2%80%99.%20%E2%80%98I%20was%20concerned%20with%20the%20unity%20of%20India.%20It%20had%20been%20lost%20now%20and%20therefore%20I%20had%20come%20to%20certain%20arrangements%20with%20Mr.%20Jinnah.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFortunately%2C%20the%20most%20valuable%20of%20Travancore%E2%80%99s%20commodities%2C%20monazite%2C%20remained%20off%20the%20table%20thanks%20to%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20quick-wittedness.%20In%201946%20and%201947%2C%20the%20leftist%20weekly%20Blitz%20had%20published%20a%20series%20of%20articles%20by%20journalist%20K.N.%20Bamzai%20exposing%20the%20secret%20negotiations%20being%20conducted%20by%20the%20maharaja%20with%20monazite-extracting%20companies.%20Under%20one%20of%20the%20deals%2C%209%2C000%20tonnes%20of%20monazite%20were%20to%20be%20sent%20to%20Britain%20over%20three%20years.%20In%20return%2C%20the%20British%20government%20had%20promised%20to%20get%20the%20company%20Thorium%20Ltd%20to%20construct%20a%20processing%20plant%20in%20the%20state.%20When%20Nehru%20read%20about%20the%20deal%2C%20he%20moved%20quickly.%20At%20the%20Indian%20Science%20Congress%20in%20January%201947%20he%20pushed%20through%20a%20resolution%20that%20the%20Indian%20state%20should%20own%20and%20control%20all%20minerals%20required%20to%20produce%20nuclear%20energy.%20Speaking%20at%20a%20cabinet%20meeting%20in%20April%201947%2C%20he%20warned%20of%20using%20air%20power%20against%20Travancore%20to%20bring%20its%20recalcitrant%20Aiyar%20and%20the%20maharaja%20to%20heel.%20Two%20months%20later%2C%20he%20sent%20Sir%20Shanti%20Swarup%20Bhatnagar%2C%20head%20of%20the%20Council%20of%20Scientific%20and%20Industrial%20Research%2C%20to%20Travancore%20to%20block%20any%20deals%20for%20export%20of%20monazite%20to%20England.%20Surprisingly%2C%20Tiruvithamkoor%20and%20Aiyar%20capitulated%20without%20a%20fight%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20establishment%20of%20the%20Travancore-India%20Joint%20Commission%20on%20Atomic%20Energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Aiyar%20knew%20of%20the%20strategic%20value%20of%20thorium%20early%20on%2C%20he%20failed%20to%20use%20it%20as%20a%20card%20to%20play%20in%20his%20state%E2%80%99s%20bid%20for%20independence.%20Writing%20to%20the%20maharaja%20a%20few%20days%20after%20the%20bombing%20of%20Nagasaki%20in%201945%2C%20he%20declared%3A%20%E2%80%98If%20thorium%20can%20be%20utilized%20for%20the%20manufacture%20of%20atomic%20bombs%20(there%20is%20no%20reason%20why%20it%20should%20not%20be)%2C%20Travancore%20will%20enjoy%20a%20very%20high%20position%20in%20the%20world.%E2%80%99%20The%20historian%20Itty%20Abraham%20speculates%20that%20Aiyar%20realized%20that%20withholding%20thorium%20to%20India%20would%20be%20a%20step%20too%20far.%20%E2%80%98Denial%20of%20a%20strategic%20resource%20would%20open%20the%20door%20to%20a%20military%20response%20against%20which%20he%20could%20not%20defend%2C%20and%20which%20he%20was%20desperately%20trying%20to%20avoid.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EExcerpted%20with%20permission%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3EDethroned%3A%20Patel%2C%20Menon%20and%20the%20Integration%20of%20Princely%20India%3Cem%3Eby%20John%20Zubrzycki%2C%20published%20by%20Juggernaut.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fjohnn%5C%22%3EJohn%20Zubrzycki%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20an%20Australia-based%20writer.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689909729000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21084954%2FBhaktivilas.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fjust-before-independence-travancore-too-declared-it-would-not-be-a-part-of-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20region%20was%20rich%20with%20resources%2C%20including%20monazite%2C%20a%20crucial%20ingredient%20in%20nuclear%20reactors%20and%20weapons.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fjust-before-independence-travancore-too-declared-it-would-not-be-a-part-of-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kalki%202898%20-%20AD%20Teaser%3A%20May%20The%20Force%20Be%20With%20Prabhas%2C%20Deepika%2C%20Big%20B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAttention%20folks%2C%20the%20makers%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fproject-k-at-comic-con-new-inside-pics-of-prabhas-and-kamal-haasan-4225912%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EProject%20K%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20dropped%20the%20teaser%20of%20the%2