20phone%20as%20%26quot%3Bfull%20stack%20serotonin%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20the%20brain%20chemical%20associated%20with%20happiness%2C%20focus%2C%20and%20calmness%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmy.clevelandclinic.org%2Fhealth%2Farticles%2F22572-serotonin%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSerotonin%2520is%2520associated%2520with%2520happiness%2Cincluding%2520depression%2520and%2520mood%2520disorders.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECleveland%20Clinic%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Mack%20said%20the%20only%20apps%20on%20this%20phone%20are%20notes%2C%20Kindle%2C%20Uber%2C%20and%20Maps%2C%20and%20that%20only%20two%20to%20three%20people%20have%20the%20number%2C%20in%20case%20of%20emergencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20cocaine%20phone%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bfull%20stack%20dopamine%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20the%20brain%20chemical%20associated%20with%20motivation%20and%20rewards.%20Social%20media%20is%20known%20to%20trigger%20the%20brain's%20reward%20system%20by%20releasing%20dopamine%20with%20each%20swipe%2C%20ultimately%20turning%20us%20all%20into%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fglobal%2F2021%2Faug%2F22%2Fhow-digital-media-turned-us-all-into-dopamine-addicts-and-what-we-can-do-to-break-the-cycle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edopamine%20junkies%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20are%20always%20craving%20just%20a%20bit%20more.%20Mack's%20cocaine%20phone%20has%20the%20time-killing%20apps%20you'd%20expect%3A%20Twitter%2C%20Instagram%2C%20TikTok%2C%20and%20WhatsApp%2C%20and%20allows%20anyone%20to%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20goes%20into%20detail%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fgeorge__mack%2Fstatus%2F1681378342627311640%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETwitter%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20how%20he%20uses%20each%20phone%2C%20but%20ultimately%20what%20kinds%20of%20phones%20you%20use%20and%20what%20you%20put%20on%20them%20will%20depend%20on%20your%20specific%20circumstances%20and%20needs.%20He%20said%20he's%20gotten%20%26quot%3Bcountless%20DM's%20of%20people%20who%20have%20said%20this%20has%20fixed%20their%20smartphone%20addiction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMack's%20not%20the%20first%20person%20to%20suggest%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Fbreak-your-phone-addiction-with-second-phone%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwo-phone%20solution%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20thinking%20about%20it%20in%20terms%20of%20kale%20and%20cocaine%2C%20or%20serotonin%20and%20dopamine%2C%20could%20be%20useful%20in%20figuring%20out%20how%20to%20divvy%20up%20your%20phone%20usage.%20The%20two%20phones%20could%20also%20help%20set%20boundaries%20about%20when%20you're%20using%20your%20phone%20as%20a%20useful%20tool%2C%20and%20when%20you're%20using%20it%20in%20ways%20that%20aren't%20a%20net%20positive%20on%20your%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20you're%20like%20the%20many%20Americans%20who%20spend%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnet.com%2Ftech%2Fservices-and-software%2Famericans-spent-a-third-of-waking-hours-on-mobile-devices-in-2021-report-finds%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethird%20of%20their%20waking%20hours%20staring%20at%20phones%20or%20tablets%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you've%20got%20nothing%20to%20lose%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20to%20gain%20by%20trying%20it%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsolve-smart-phone-addiction-getting-2-phones-fun-work-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689903109000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b9cd26006a5e00194969c1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsolve-smart-phone-addiction-getting-2-phones-fun-work-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Many%20Americans%20spends%20hours%20a%20day%20staring%20at%20their%20cell%20phones%2C%20but%20having%20two%20separate%20phones%20for%20different%20purposes%20could%20help%20you%20set%20boundaries.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40insider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsolve-smart-phone-addiction-getting-2-phones-fun-work-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Natural%20Farming%20Can%20Revive%20India%E2%80%99s%20Farmlands%20and%20Ensure%20Sustainable%20Agriculture%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F09%2Frepresentative-image-of-farming-in-Assam-Photo-PTI.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20after%20becoming%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsociety%2Findia-china-highest-populated%5C%22%3Emost%20populous%20country%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20facing%20a%20paradoxical%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20population%20grows%2C%20an%20increasing%20number%20of%20people%20are%20moving%20away%20from%20farm%20jobs.%20According%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fover-50-per-cent-agricultural-families-in-debt-with-average-loan-of-rs-74121-in-2019-survey%2Farticleshow%2F86098176.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3E2019%20National%20Sample%20Survey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20farmers%20are%20debt-ridden%20and%20often%20seek%20alternatives%20outside%20of%20agriculture%2C%20or%20tragically%2C%20end%20their%20own%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20malady%20lies%20in%20acidified%20and%20depleted%20soil%2C%20extreme%20and%20changing%20climate%20patterns%2C%20growing%20crop%20pests%2C%20deteriorating%20agriculture-supporting%20ecosystem%20services%2C%20and%20poor%20groundwater%20conditions%2C%20all%20of%20which%20contribute%20to%20low%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20address%20these%20issues%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%20is%20promoting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Fnews%2Fagriculture%2Frestore-by-use-regenerative-agriculture-can-help-save-water-here-is-how-86065%5C%22%3Enatural%2C%20or%20regenerative%20farming%3C%2Fa%3E%20practices%20that%20are%20environment-friendly%20and%20rely%20on%20traditional%20methods%20without%20chemical%20additives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERegenerative%20agriculture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20research%20shows%20that%20natural%20farming%20boosts%20soil%20microbial%20health%20by%20fostering%20a%20more%20heterogeneous%20population%20of%20bacteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20use%20of%20organic%20and%20natural%20amendments%20in%20this%20farming%20practice%20nurtures%20healthy%20growth%20of%20all%20biodiversity%2C%20including%20bacteria.%20The%20thriving%20community%20of%20bacteria%20breaks%20down%20complex%20organic%20matter%20into%20simple%20forms%20that%20can%20be%20easily%20absorbed%20by%20plant%20roots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20these%20bacteria%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclimate.mit.edu%2Fexplainers%2Fsoil-based-carbon-sequestration%5C%22%3Esequester%3C%2Fa%3E%20atmospheric%20nitrogen%20and%20carbon%20in%20the%20soil%20through%20mechanisms%20such%20as%20nitrogen%20fixation%20and%20photosynthesis%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FB9780128141243000303%5C%22%3Echemolithoautotrophy%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20diverse%20group%20of%20bacteria%20creates%20a%20robust%20environment%20that%20can%20overcome%20multiple%20environmental%20and%20pathogen-based%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20enriched%20bacterial%20pool%20enhances%20the%20soil%E2%80%99s%20nutritional%20composition%20for%20better%20plant%20growth%2C%20and%20competitively%20represses%20plant%20pathogens%20and%20soil-degrading%20microbes%2C%20and%20provides%20plants%20innate%20immunity%20against%20pests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20interesting%20facet%20of%20regenerative%20agriculture%20is%20the%20use%20of%20mixed%2C%20inter%20and%20multi-cropping%20practices.%20These%20practices%20help%20improve%20soil%20health%20as%20each%20crop%20type%20introduces%20a%20varied%20population%20of%20microbiome%20to%20the%20soil.%20Additionally%2C%20mixed%20cropping%20helps%20evade%20pests%20and%20pathogens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESoil%20health%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaryana%20stands%20out%20as%20the%20only%20state%20that%20has%20introduced%20incentives%20for%20promoting%20crop%20diversification.%20In%20March%20this%20year%2C%20the%20state%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fchandigarh-news%2Fachieve-zero-stubble-burning-haryana-told-101680118379988.html%5C%22%3Eprovided%3C%2Fa%3E%20Rs%2041.42%20crore%20to%2034%2C239%20farmers%20for%20adopting%20crop%20diversification.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBuilding%20on%20our%20research%20findings%2C%20this%20policy%20highlights%20the%20need%20to%20promote%20and%20enable%20natural%20farming%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20endeavour%20requires%20conducting%20training%20camps%20for%20all%20stakeholders%2C%20educating%20farmers%20about%20the%20practices%20that%20can%20improve%20soil%20health%2C%20providing%20high-quality%20seeds%2C%20establishing%20farmer%20cooperatives%20to%20offer%20necessary%20advice%2C%20support%20and%20material%2C%20incentivising%20natural%20agriculture%20through%20various%20schemes%2C%20and%20establishing%20market%20linkages%20for%20sustainable%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20natural%20farming%20approach%20is%20sometimes%20misunderstood%20as%20%E2%80%98zero-budget%E2%80%99%2C%20meeting%20the%20demands%20of%20high-yield%20farming%20needs%20substantial%20organic%20supplementation%20or%20even%20cow%20dung%2C%20a%20crucial%20component%20of%20traditional%20mixtures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fkashmir-saffron-farmers-indoor-farming%5C%22%3EKashmir%3A%20Saffron%20Farmers%20Fight%20Climate%20Change%20With%20Indoor%20Farming%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EZero-budget%20natural%20farming%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fsci-tech%2Fagriculture%2Fwhat-is-zero-budget-natural-farming%2Farticle61590716.ece%5C%22%3Eprocess%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20raising%20crops%20without%20using%20chemical%20fertilisers%20and%20pesticides%20or%20any%20other%20external%20materials.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20soil%20organic%20carbon%20(SOC)%20levels%20currently%20stand%20below%20the%20ideal%20levels%20(%26lt%3B%200.5%25)%20due%20to%20unsustainable%20agricultural%20practices.%20However%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20note%20that%20four%20times%20more%20organic%20supplementation%20is%20needed%20in%20the%20initial%20years%20to%20meet%20plant%20nutrient%20requirements%20compared%20to%20chemical%20fertilisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnlike%20chemical%20fertilisers%20that%20are%20directly%20absorbed%20by%20the%20plant%20roots%2C%20organic%20amendments%20must%20be%20broken%20down%20into%20easily%20available%20forms.%20This%20breakdown%20process%20helps%20build%20a%20thriving%20microbial%20system%20in%20the%20soil%2C%20which%20has%20a%20lasting%20impact%20on%20soil%20health.%20Therefore%2C%20reviving%20India%E2%80%99s%20farmlands%20require%20heavy%20input%20of%20amendments%20during%20the%20initial%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20our%20own%20study%2C%20we%20found%20that%20the%20farm%20with%20the%20best%20microbial%20and%20nutrient%20profile%20had%20been%20applying%20heavy%20organic%20amendments%20for%20ten%20years%2C%20mainly%20using%20cow%20dung%20for%20soil%20health%20and%20%3Cem%3Ejeevamrutha%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20fermented%20mixture%20containing%20chickpea%20flour%2C%20jaggery%2C%20cow%20dung%2C%20cow%20urine%20and%20soil)%20for%20pest%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20farm%20displayed%20the%20highest%20SOC%20levels%20at%200.51%25%2C%20a%20significant%20improvement%20compared%20to%20the%20Indian%20average%20of%200.3%25%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20the%20National%20Rainfed%20Area%20Authority%20(NRAA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20this%20farm%20reported%20a%20significant%20increase%20in%20crop%20productivity%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20study%20found%20adopting%20natural%20farming%20for%20more%20than%20five%20years%20has%20a%20positive%20cumulative%20effect%20on%20both%20soil%20microbial%20health%20and%20crop%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20initial%20years%20of%20transitioning%2C%20when%20soil%20communities%20are%20evolving%20and%20soil%20health%20is%20being%20rejuvenated%2C%20the%20bacterial%20diversity%20and%20crop%20productivity%20would%20be%20less.%20In%20such%20cases%2C%20supplementing%20the%20land%20with%20moderate%20amounts%20of%20chemical%20fertilisation%20can%20be%20beneficial%20in%20supporting%20crop%20yields.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChemical%20fertilisation%20can%20be%20tapered%20down%20with%20time.%20After%20a%20period%20of%20eight%20to%20ten%20years%2C%20natural%20farming%20will%20alone%20be%20capable%20of%20sustaining%20high%20crop%20productivity%20without%20the%20use%20of%20any%20chemical%20fertilisers.%20Chemical%20pesticides%20should%20be%20strictly%20avoided%20throughout%20the%20process%2C%20and%20instead%2C%20biopesticides%2C%3Cem%3E%20jeevamrutha%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20light%20traps%20for%20insect%20pests%20can%20be%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMulching%20with%20green%20manure%20like%20Dhaincha%20(Sesbania%20aculeata)%20is%20another%20method%20to%20rejuvenate%20and%20enhance%20carbon%2Fbiomass%20and%20mineral%20content%20in%20the%20soil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EData%20shows%20that%20organic%20fertilisation%20not%20only%20fortifies%20the%20soil%20with%20nutrients%20but%20also%20improves%20its%20porosity%2C%20texture%2C%20water%20and%20nutrient%20retention%20abilities%2C%20and%20microbial%20community%20structure%2C%20creating%20a%20sustainable%20impact%20on%20soil%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20healthy%20and%20diverse%20soil%20microbial%20population%20provides%20plants%20with%20a%20steady%20supply%20of%20nutrients%2C%20maintains%20soil%20organic%20carbon%20levels%20to%20support%20plant%20growth%20and%20productivity%2C%20regulates%20soil%20moisture%20levels%20during%20periods%20of%20poor%20water%20availability%2C%20and%20protects%20plants%20against%20pests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20question%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20addressed%20is%20the%20procurement%20of%20organic%20amendments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIntegrating%20livestock%20and%20crops%2C%20a%20common%20practice%20in%20the%20past%2C%20is%20a%20viable%20option%20that%20all%20farmers%20should%20adopt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20approach%20offers%20multidimensional%20benefits%2C%20including%20income%20security%2C%20continued%20availability%20of%20animal%20manure%2C%20and%20reduced%20dependency%20on%20crops%20for%20livelihoods.%20Government%20incentives%2C%20awareness%20campaigns%2C%20and%20training%20programmes%20can%20help%20farmers%20revive%20this%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELocal%20governments%20should%20promote%20initiatives%20to%20facilitate%20the%20collection%2C%20processing%2C%20and%20distribution%20of%20cow%20dung%20and%20compost%2C%20connecting%20them%20with%20local%20Farmer%20Producer%20Organisations%20(FPOs).%20Partnerships%20with%20dairy%20farms%20and%20waste%20management%20agencies%20can%20establish%20a%20sustainable%20supply%20chain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Findias-agriculture-is-feeling-the-effects-of-extreme-weather-events%5C%22%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20Agriculture%20Is%20Feeling%20the%20Effects%20of%20Extreme%20Weather%20Events%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaximising%20resource%20utilisation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20cities%20like%20Bengaluru%2C%20environmentally%20conscious%20citizens%20are%20already%20conducting%20apartment-level%20decentralised%20green%20waste%20composting.%20Peri-urban%20farmers%20bring%20their%20trucks%20loaded%20with%20produce%20and%20return%20with%20the%20%E2%80%98black%20gold%E2%80%99.%20This%20exchange%20of%20food%20for%20compost%20could%20become%20the%20norm%20for%20all%20apartments%20in%20Indian%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESmaller%20apartments%20and%20individual%20houses%20should%20share%20compost%20units%2C%20which%20should%20be%20included%20in%20colony%20planning.%20Local%20authorities%20should%20support%20and%20incentivise%20such%20initiatives%2C%20providing%20the%20necessary%20infrastructure%20and%20guidance%20for%20widespread%20adoption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEstablishing%20efficient%20channels%20for%20transporting%20compost%20generated%20from%20decentralised%20green%20waste%20management%20units%20to%20farmers%20is%20vital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECollaborations%20between%20waste%20management%20agencies%2C%20transport%20companies%2C%20state%20government%20agricultural%20agencies%2C%20and%20FPOs%20can%20ensure%20a%20smooth%20and%20cost-effective%20distribution%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20facilitating%20the%20seamless%20flow%20of%20compost%20from%20urban%20areas%20to%20agricultural%20lands%2C%20this%20approach%20maximises%20resource%20utilisation%20and%20strengthens%20the%20symbiotic%20relationship%20between%20urban%20and%20rural%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20problem%20of%20stubble%20burning%20and%20associated%20poor%20air%20quality%20in%20the%20Delhi-NCR%20region%20can%20be%20managed%20by%20training%20farmers%20on%20the%20benefits%20of%20mulching%20crop%20residues%20directly%20into%20the%20soil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20the%20Haryana%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fagriharyana.gov.in%2FCRMCombineStraw%5C%22%3Eincentivised%3C%2Fa%3E%20sustainable%20in-situ%2Fex-situ%20management%20of%20crop%20residue%20to%20prevent%20stubble%20burning%20by%20offering%20farmers%20Rs%201%2C000%20per%20acre.%20The%20government%20claims%20that%20the%20scheme%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fchandigarh-news%2Fachieve-zero-stubble-burning-haryana-told-101680118379988.html%5C%22%3E%20has%20reduced%3C%2Fa%3E%20farm%20fires%20by%2045%25%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETraining%20farmers%20to%20use%20crop%20residue%20as%20a%20resource%20rather%20than%20waste%20can%20help%20them%20start%20their%20own%20vermicompost%20system%20and%20use%20the%20crop%20residue%20to%20support%20the%20next%20crop.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGovernment%20bodies%20should%20prioritise%20subsidising%20compost%20production%20and%20distribution%2C%20particularly%20for%20smallholder%20and%20resource-constrained%20farmers.%20Long-term%20contracts%20and%20partnerships%20between%20waste%20management%20agencies%20and%20farmers%20can%20stabilise%20compost%20prices%2C%20ensuring%20continued%20availability%20while%20incentivising%20sustainable%20waste%20management%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20affordable%20pricing%20of%20compost%20and%20training%20programmes%20for%20farmers%20will%20foster%20inclusivity%20and%20knowledge-sharing.%20Embracing%20these%20management%20requirements%20will%20not%20only%20mitigate%20the%20environmental%20impacts%20of%20conventional%20agriculture%20but%20also%20lead%20us%20toward%20a%20more%20resilient%2C%20equitable%2C%20and%20regenerative%20food%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIndira%20Singh%20is%20lead%20at%20the%20School%20for%20Environment%20and%20Sustainability%20at%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20for%20Human%20Settlements%2C%20Bengaluru.%20She%20is%20a%20trained%20geneticist%20and%20is%20interested%20in%20sustainability%20in%20agriculture.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689903016000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F09%2Frepresentative-image-of-farming-in-Assam-Photo-PTI.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%