2ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Some%20workers%20are%20going%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20into%20debt%20to%20pay%20for%20their%20own%20training.%20A%20federal%20watchdog%20is%20scrutinizing%20the%20practice%20of%20chasing%20employees%20for%20money%20after%20they%20leave.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223992%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Consumer%20Finanial%20Protection%20Bureau%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60dc8740cad1220011caf320%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222656%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%20headquarters%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3Cp%3EBill%20Clark%2FCQ-Roll%20Call%2C%20Inc%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20new%20report%20from%20the%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%20looks%20at%20employer-driven%20debt.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20report%20finds%20that%20employers%20are%20saddling%20workers%20with%20thousands%20in%20debt%20for%20training%20and%20supplies.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt%20means%20workers%20might%20be%20stuck%20in%20roles%20they%20no%20longer%20want%20until%20they%20can%20pay%20off%20that%20debt.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20workers%20might%20decide%20they%20want%20to%20leave%20their%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20only%20to%20get%20hit%20with%20a%20bill%20for%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20to%20compensate%20their%20former%20employer%20for%20training.%20A%20federal%20watchdog%20is%20looking%20into%20that%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20the%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%20released%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.consumerfinance.gov%2Fdata-research%2Fresearch-reports%2Fissue-spotlight-consumer-risks-posed-by-employer-driven-debt%2Ffull-report%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20detailing%20the%20impact%20of%20training%20repayment%20agreement%20provisions%2C%20or%20TRAPs.%20TRAPs%20are%20a%20form%20of%20employer-driven%20debt%20in%20which%20workers%20are%20indebted%20to%20their%20employer%20to%20cover%20the%20cost%20of%20training%2C%20equipment%2C%20or%20supplies%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20industry.%20For%20example%2C%20workers%20in%20the%20the%20rideshare%20or%20trucking%20industries%20sign%20TRAPs%20to%20get%20necessary%20transport%20supplies%20from%20their%20employer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%C2%A0the%20CFPB%C2%A0argued%C2%A0those%20agreements%20can%20harm%20workers%20because%20%26quot%3Bemployer-driven%20debts%20are%20inextricably%20linked%20to%20a%20worker's%20employment%2C%20and%20the%20worker's%20ability%20to%20repay%20the%20debt%20is%20controlled%20by%20the%20issuer%20of%20the%20debt%20itself%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20watchdog%20launched%20an%20inquiry%20to%20seek%20data%20regarding%20workers'%20experiences%20with%20TRAPs%2C%20and%20it%20found%20a%20number%20of%20risks%20those%20agreements%20are%20posing%20to%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20employees%20might%20be%20%26quot%3Brushed%20into%20signing%20agreements%20that%20hide%20the%20details%20of%20the%20debt%20workers%20are%20agreeing%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20leaving%20them%20unaware%20of%20the%20implications%20of%20the%20debt%20they%20are%20taking%20on.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20worker%20told%20the%20CFPB%20in%20a%20comment%20that%20%26quot%3B%5Ba%5Dfter%20completing%204%20years%20of%20schooling%20and%20passing%20technical%20interviews%20my%20first%20job%20seemed%20great.%20Once%20onboarding%20I%20discovered%20some%20'training'%20was%20required%2C%20no%20problem%20at%20all.%20However%20the%20first%20day%20consisted%20of%20signing%20a%20long%20employment%20document%20in%20a%20room%20with%20all%20the%20other%20employees%20that%20required%20%2410%2C000%20to%20be%20paid%20by%20us%20if%20we%20leave%20the%20company%20within%20a%20year%20and%20%245%2C000%20if%20within%202%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20those%20workers%20might%20have%20to%20stay%20at%20the%20job%20even%20if%20they%20want%20to%20leave%20because%20they%20cannot%20afford%20to%20repay%20that%20debt.%20Another%20worker%20told%20the%20CFPB%20in%20a%20comment%20that%20%26quot%3Bif%20I%20mention%20being%20unhappy%2C%20my%20boss%20replies%20that%20they'll%20take%20me%20to%20court%20for%20the%20over%20%245%2C000%20they%20say%20I%20owe%20since%20it%20hasn't%20been%20two%20years.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20a%20different%20worker%20ended%20up%20returning%20to%20her%20job%20after%20leaving%2C%20saying%20in%20a%20comment%3A%20%3Cem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3EShortly%20after%20they%20left%2C%20Nurse%20E%20received%20a%20collection%20letter%20notifying%20them%20that%20they%20either%20pay%20the%20hospital%20%2418%2C000%2C%20which%20was%20what%20%5Bcompany%5D%20said%20was%20the%20prorated%20cost%20of%20their%20training%2C%20or%20complete%20the%20two-year%2F4%2C000-hour%20requirement.%20Nurse%20E%20tried%20to%20negotiate%20the%20payment%20of%20the%20amount%20they%20owed%2C%20but%20the%20hospital%20refused%E2%80%A6Nurse%20E%20decided%20to%20return%20to%20working%20at%20%5Bredacted%5D%20because%20of%20the%20financial%20liability.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20workers'%20claims%20of%20misleading%20terms%20on%20TRAPs%2C%20the%20CFPB%20also%20said%20workers%20experience%20lower%20earnings%20under%20these%20agreements%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20deductions%20are%20taken%20to%20cover%20debt%20payments%20throughout%20the%20course%20of%20their%20work%20or%20to%20cover%20additional%20significant%20employment-related%20expenses.%26quot%3B%20The%20watchdog%20said%20it%20will%20continue%20to%20evaluate%20how%20companies%20are%20using%20TRAPs%20to%20determine%20whether%20they%20are%20violating%20consumer%20financial%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20CFPB%20probe%20comes%20amidst%20a%20Biden-administration-wide%20crackdown%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-new-plan-to-save-renters-from-bogus-apartment-fees-2023-7%5C%22%3Eunnecessary%20fees%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20contracts%20that%20keep%20workers%20in%20low-paying%20jobs.%20In%20January%2C%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fftc-wants-ban-noncompete-agreements-workers-make-300-billion-more-2023-1%5C%22%3Eproposed%20a%20rule%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20would%20ban%20noncompetes%20%E2%80%94%20clauses%20in%20contracts%20that%20prohibit%20workers%20from%20taking%20jobs%20in%20similar%20industries%20or%20starting%20their%20own%20businesses%20in%20the%20same%20field.%20The%20FTC%20estimated%20that%20banning%20noncompetes%20could%20put%20nearly%20%24300%20billion%20more%20in%20workers'%20pockets%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BThe%20abusive%20practices%20uncovered%20by%20the%20Bureau%20should%20be%20a%20wake%20up%20call%20to%20consumer%20protection%20officials%20and%20policymakers%20at%20all%20levels%2C%26quot%3B%20advocacy%20group%20Student%20Borrower%20Protection%20Center%20Deputy%20Executive%20Director%20and%20Managing%20Counsel%20Persis%20Yu%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BTRAPs%20impose%20significant%20financial%20burdens%20on%20workers%20and%20foster%20monopsony%20in%20labor%20markets%20by%20reducing%20worker%20mobility%20and%20bargaining%20power.%20The%20largest%20corporations%20in%20America%20are%20now%20on%20notice%3A%20the%20use%20of%20TRAPs%20and%20other%20predatory%20contract%20terms%20must%20stop.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-are-traps-employer-driven-debt-cfpb-repayment-agreement-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689883797000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61eec758d2653000180459de%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-are-traps-employer-driven-debt-cfpb-repayment-agreement-2023-7%22%2C%22summary