d%20and%20Department%20of%20Public%20Safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20miles%20of%20concertina%20wire%20%E2%80%94%20a%20type%20of%20razor%20wire%20%E2%80%94%20and%20large%20orange%20buoys%20were%20installed%20to%20deter%20migrants%20crossing%20through%20the%20Rio%20Grande%20River%20near%20the%20city%20of%20Eagle%20Pass.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20new%20measures%20have%20been%20implemented%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20source%20cited%20by%20the%20Chronicle%20several%20other%20state%20troopers%20have%20raised%20concerns%20against%20the%20governor's%20aggressive%20approach%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F07%2F19%2Fus%2Ftexas-border-migrants-abbott.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20memo%20to%20the%20state's%20Department%20of%20Public%20Safety%20that%20was%20obtained%20by%20The%20Times%2C%20US%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EBorder%20Patrol%20officials%20have%20also%20raised%20concerns%20about%20razor%20wire%20placed%20along%20the%20river%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20wire%20creates%20hazardous%20conditions%20for%20the%20migrants%20and%20border%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224254%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Large%20orange%20buoys%20float%20behind%20migrants%20walking%20in%20the%20river.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b879e68a4e660019e3bbdf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223190%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMigrants%20crossing%20the%20Rio%20Grande%20from%20Mexico%20walk%20past%20large%20orange%20buoys%20deployed%20by%20Texas%20border%20security.%3Cp%3EEric%20Gay%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Texas%20trooper%20provided%20accounts%20of%20migrants%20getting%20caught%20in%20the%20razor%20wire%20and%20being%20ordered%20to%20deny%20people%20drinking%20water%20while%20weathering%20the%20extreme%20heat%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noo