20the%20case%20for%20India.%20He%20said%20Germany%20and%20India%20want%20to%20strengthen%20economic%20cooperation%2C%20including%20creating%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccommon%20trade%20sphere%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20could%20be%20the%20answer%20to%20reducing%20dependence%20on%20one%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHabeck%20was%20speaking%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20Indo-German%20Business%20Forum%20and%20is%20in%20India%20for%20a%20three-day%20visit.%20He%20later%20met%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20and%20is%20scheduled%20to%20meet%20commerce%20and%20industry%20minister%20Piyush%20Goyal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaishankar%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDrSJaishankar%2Fstatus%2F1682001150747488256%5C%22%3Etweeted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20had%20a%20%E2%80%9Cproductive%20discussion%20on%20the%20many%20new%20opportunities%20of%20India-Germany%20cooperation%20that%20a%20rising%20India%20presents%E2%80%9D.%20The%20two%20ministers%20also%C2%A0exchanged%20perspectives%20on%20the%20conflict%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20situation%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Finternational%2Fwe-cant-decouple-from-china-german-vice-chancellor-dr-robert-habeck%2Farticle67100970.ece%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Habeck%20%E2%80%93%20who%20is%20also%20the%20German%20federal%20minister%20for%20economic%20affairs%20and%20climate%20action%20%E2%80%93%20said%20that%20his%20country%E2%80%99s%20partnership%20with%20China%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccomplicated%20one%E2%80%9D.%20Beijing%20is%20Berlin%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20trading%20partner%20and%20%E2%80%9Ca%20lot%20of%20companies%2C%20German%2C%20European%20companies%20have%20invested%20in%20China%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20Therefore%2C%20Germany%20cannot%20decouple%20from%20China%20and%20%E2%80%9Cnobody%20wants%20that%E2%80%9D%20but%20%E2%80%9Cde-risking%2C%20diversification%20is%20of%20the%20highest%20importance%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20being%20dependent%20on%20%E2%80%9Conly%20one%20market%E2%80%9D%20could%20be%20a%20risk%2C%20especially%20if%20countries%20see%20that%20economic%20issues%20are%20not%20politically%20neutral%2C%20Habeck%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Feconomy%2Fforeign-trade%2Findia-germany-to-strengthen-bilateral-ties-increase-investments-german-vice-chancellor%2Farticleshow%2F101981984.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20diversification%2C%20partnerships%20like%20the%20Indo-German%20partnership%20will%20become%20%E2%80%9Cmore%20and%20more%20important%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20vice-chancellor%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20understanding%20also%20from%20the%20talks%20ahead%20with%20the%20Indian%20partners%20is%2C%20that%20goes%20the%20same%20for%20India.%20So%20there%20is%20a%20mutual%20interest%20from%20the%20German%20side%20and%20the%20Indian%20side%20to%20strengthen%20our%20cooperation%20and%20bringing%20more%20companies%20together%2C%20bringing%20more%20investments%2C%20creating%20a%20common%20trade%20sphere%20also%20as%20an%20answer%20that%20we%20are%20not%20becoming%20too%20dependent%20on%20only%20one%20country%20and%20from%20the%20German%20side%20that%20is%20also%20China%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20was%20quoted%20as%20saying%20by%20%3Cem%3EET%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minister%20also%20discussed%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20urging%20democracies%20to%20%E2%80%9Cabide%20by%20the%20sanctions%20imposed%20on%20Russia%E2%80%9D%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Russian%20aggression%20on%20Ukraine%20is%20unprecedented.%20..We%20answered%20with%20sanctions%20against%20it%20and%20also%20with%20military%20support%20for%20Ukraine.%20The%20sanction%20system%20means%20that%20we%20have%20not%20bent%20the%20trade%20of%20oil%20but%20there%20is%20a%20price%20cap%20on%20it.%20That%20means%20that%20you%20are%20allowed%20to%20buy%20crude%20oil%20and%20recognise%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20okay.%20But%20making%20money%20out%20of%20it%2C%20bringing%20more%20money%20to%20Russia%20using%20this%20sanction%20system%20to%20benefit%20from%20it%20is%20not%20the%20idea%20of%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEver%20since%20the%20war%20began%20in%20February%202022%2C%20India%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20purchasers%20of%20Russian%20crude.%20Several%20companies%20have%20also%20sold%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Feuropean-union-india-reselling-russian-crude-refined%5C%22%3Erefined%20crude%20to%20European%20nations%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20profit.%20India%20has%20defended%20these%20purchases%2C%20saying%20it%20protects%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20energy%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20German%20vice-chancellor%20also%20said%20that%20though%20%E2%80%9CEurope%20is%20a%20little%20bit%20away%20from%20Asia%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20conflict%20is%20of%20such%20importance%20that%20%E2%80%9Call%20democracies%E2%80%9D%20should%20to%20be%20clear%20in%20language%20and%20political%20position%20that%20this%20is%20not%20acceptable%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EET%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHabeck%20described%20the%20ongoing%20negotiation%20between%20India%20and%20the%20European%20Union%20(EU)%20over%20a%20free%20trade%20agreement%20as%20%E2%80%9Cdifficult%E2%80%9D.%20The%20economic%20traditions%20and%20expectations%20of%20India%20and%20the%20EU%20are%20different%2C%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9COne%20side%20is%20expecting%20more%20openness%20and%20intellectual%20property%20and%20the%20other%20side%20is%20expecting%20more%20market%20access%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EET%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20he%20refused%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20ethnic%20clashes%20in%20Manipur%2C%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20not%20on%20the%20table%20for%20me.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHabeck%E2%80%99s%20reference%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20purchase%20of%20Russian%20crude%20was%20not%20well%20received%20by%20Moscow%E2%80%99s%20envoy%20in%20India%20Denis%20Alipov.%20%E2%80%9CNoted%20reports%20that%20one%20of%20the%20goals%20of%20German%20Vice%20Chancellor%20Robert%20Habeck%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20India%20is%20to%20discuss%20Russia-India%20cooperation.%20He%E2%80%99d%20do%20better%20to%20concentrate%20on%20India-Germany%20relations%20instead%20as%20he%E2%80%99s%20supposed%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20tweeted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlipov%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FAmbRus_India%2Fstatus%2F1681983023032733698%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9CGermany%20has%20abandoned%20independent%20position%20on%20security%20issues%20in%20Europe%20making%20its%20voice%20in%20the%20Ukrainian%20conflict%20irrelevant.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689864343000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F20200041%2F46687148461_fbe2698d74_k.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fgermany-china-india-diversify-robert-habeck%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Robert%20Habeck%20said%20that%20India%20and%20Germany%20plan%20to%20strengthen%20cooperation%20and%20increase%20investment.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fgermany-china-india-diversify-robert-habeck%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian%20Democracy%E2%80%99s%20Chance%20of%20Surviving%20Is%20Brightening%2C%20but%20There%20Is%20No%20Room%20for%20Complacency%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F15203328%2F2022_8img15_Aug_2022_PTI08_15_2022_000321B-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20fact%20that%20ten%20more%20%E2%80%98like-minded%E2%80%99%20parties%20have%20joined%20the%20meeting%20of%20the%20opposition%20at%20Bengaluru%2C%20that%20the%20Congress%20has%20graciously%20met%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%E2%80%99s%20demand%20that%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fahead-of-second-opposition-meet-congress-says-it-will-not-support-delhi-ordinance%5C%22%3Ecommits%20itself%20to%20voting%20against%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Bill%20that%20seeks%20to%20deprive%20the%20Delhi%20government%20of%20control%20over%20its%20own%20civil%20servants%2C%C2%A0%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20and%20that%20the%20opposition%20has%20now%20given%20itself%20a%20single%20name%20%E2%80%93%20INDIA%20%E2%80%93%20reflects%20the%20near-complete%20consensus%20within%20the%20opposition%20on%20the%20need%20to%20set%20differences%20aside%20in%20order%20to%20save%20democracy.%20This%20has%20greatly%20increased%20the%20likelihood%20of%20a%20defeat%20for%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%202024%20Lok%20sabha%20election%2C%20by%20shifting%20the%20%E2%80%98multiplier%20effect%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20simple%20majority%20voting%20system%2C%20which%20invariably%20magnifies%20the%20seat-to-vote%20ratio%20of%20the%20largest%20party%20or%20coalition%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20smaller%20ones%2C%20in%20the%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20favour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20past%20two%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20this%20effect%20worked%20strongly%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20BJP.%20In%202014%2C%20its%2031%25%20vote%20share%20made%20it%20the%20largest%20single%20party%20in%20the%20elections.%20That%2C%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20all%20but%20a%20fraction%20of%20this%20vote%20was%20concentrated%20in%20seven%20states%20of%20northern%20and%20western%20India%20enabled%20it%20to%20win%20282%20seats%2C%20comprising%2052%25%20of%20the%20total%20membership%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20In%202019%2C%20its%20vote%20share%20increased%20to%2037%25%2C%20close%20to%20double%20that%20of%20the%20next%20largest%20party%2C%20the%20Congress.%20That%20enabled%20it%20to%20win%20303%20seats.%20Opposition%20unity%20next%20year%20will%20take%20the%20multiplier%20effect%20away%20from%20the%20BJP%20and%20confer%20it%20upon%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F20153304%2FF1UU3_DaAAE1uwZ.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F20153304%2FF1UU3_DaAAE1uwZ.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F20153304%2FF1UU3_DaAAE1uwZ-300x139.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F20153304%2FF1UU3_DaAAE1uwZ-1024x474.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-664153%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22556%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EJoint%20opposition%20parties%20meeting%20in%20Bengaluru.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40AAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHow%20dramatic%20this%20shift%20can%20be%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdecoding-the-karnataka-election-results-in-18-charts%5C%22%3Evividly%20demonstrated%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Karnataka%20Vidhan%20Sabha%20elections%20in%20May.%20Although%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20the%20vote%20remained%20unchanged%20at%2036%25%2C%20a%205.4%25%20shift%20of%20the%20vote%20from%20the%20JDS%20to%20the%20Congress%20%E2%80%93%20which%20increased%20its%20share%20to%2043%25%20%E2%80%93%20increased%20the%20number%20of%20seats%20it%20won%20from%2080%20to%20135%2C%20and%20brought%20down%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20tally%20from%20104%20to%2066.%20Opposition%20unity%2C%20even%20if%20not%20complete%2C%C2%A0%20will%20almost%20certainly%20do%20the%20same%20thing%20at%20the%20national%20level%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThis%20possibility%20has%20already%20driven%20Modi%20into%20a%20frenetic%20election%20mode%2C%20in%20which%20he%20has%20left%20governance%20to%20his%20lieutenants%2C%20and%20has%20been%20tailoring%20his%20every%20statement%20and%20action%20to%20creating%20a%20God-like%20image%20of%20himself%20for%20the%20ordinary%20Indian%2C%20and%20pandering%20to%20the%20hyper-nationalism%20that%20is%20latent%20in%20most%20Hindus%20in%20the%20country.%20He%20is%20not%20doing%20this%20solely%20out%20of%20a%20desire%20to%20remain%20in%20power.%20He%20is%20also%20aware%20that%20should%20the%20BJP%20lose%2C%20the%20ghosts%20of%20those%20who%20were%20killed%20in%20the%20Gujarat%20riots%2C%20and%20the%20faked%20encounters%20and%20the%20unexplained%20deaths%20that%20followed%2C%20will%20rise%20to%20torment%20him%2C%20possibly%20till%20the%20end%20of%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThis%20fusion%20of%20political%20with%20personal%20motives%20will%20make%20the%202024%20elections%20the%20most%20fateful%20that%20India%20has%20ever%20faced.%20For%2C%20democracies%20can%20only%20survive%20if%20their%20leaders%20are%20willing%20to%20accept%20defeat%20and%20fight%20for%20power%20through%20the%20ballot%2C%20instead%20of%20the%20bullet.%20Modi%20has%20shown%20a%20reluctance%20to%20do%20this%20throughout%20the%2022%20years%20he%20has%20enjoyed%20power%20at%20Gandhinagar%20and%20Delhi.%20He%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20certain%20to%20seize%20any%20opportunity%20that%20arises%20in%20the%20next%20nine%20months%20to%20pose%20again%20as%20the%20guardian%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20security%20and%20honour%2C%20as%20he%20was%20able%20to%20do%20after%20the%20Pulwama%20suicide%20bombing%20in%20February%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EModi%20may%20sense%20an%20opportunity%20in%20Kashmir%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOne%20such%20opportunity%20is%20certain%20to%20arise%20in%20Kashmir%20%E2%80%93%20if%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20rules%20against%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%202019%20abolition%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20special%20status%20under%20Article%20370%2C%20and%20rules%20that%20it%20must%20be%20re-instated.%20The%20court%E2%80%99s%20brusque%20dismissal%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20attempt%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-article-370-kashmir-jammu%5C%22%3Ejustify%20that%20action%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20claiming%2C%20ex-post%2C%20that%20it%20has%20brought%20peace%20and%20economic%20development%20to%20the%20state%2C%20has%20aroused%20this%20hope%20in%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20political%20parties%2C%20and%20public%2C%20throughout%20the%20Valley.%20Should%20it%20do%20so%2C%20they%20believe%20that%20Delhi%20will%20have%20no%20option%20but%20to%20restore%20the%20%3Cem%3Estatus%20quo%20ante%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20thereby%20restore%20their%20right%20to%20preserve%20their%20ethnic%20identity%20within%20the%20Indian%20union.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EBut%20they%20could%20be%20catastrophically%20wrong.%20In%20his%2022%20years%20of%20leadership%2C%20Modi%20has%20never%2C%20ever%2C%20admitted%20that%20he%20has%20made%20a%20mistake%20that%20needs%20correction.%20Nor%20has%20he%20ever%20reversed%20any%20decision%20he%20has%20taken.%20So%2C%20how%20is%20he%20likely%20to%20react%20to%20such%20a%20direct%20challenge%20to%20his%20authority%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHad%20the%20petitions%20against%20the%20dilution%20of%20Article%20370%20been%20filed%20in%20a%20lower%20court%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20high%20court%2C%20Modi%20would%20have%20been%20able%20to%20buy%20time%20till%20after%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20by%20appealing%20against%20an%20adverse%20order%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20But%20all%20of%20them%20were%20lodged%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20which%20is%20the%20court%20of%20final%20appeal%2C%20so%20the%20only%20alternative%20that%20will%20be%20available%20to%20Modi%20is%20to%20assert%20parliament%E2%80%99s%20supremacy%20over%20every%20other%20democratic%20institution%20in%20the%20country%2C%20as%20his%20government%20has%20done%20more%20than%20once%20in%20recent%20months%2C%20ignore%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20and%20continue%20to%20rule%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20directly%20from%20Delhi.%20This%20will%20almost%20certainly%20make%20the%20simmering%20discontent%20in%20the%20Valley%20explode%20into%20violence%2C%20and%20in%20doing%20so%2C%20give%20Modi%20the%20excuse%20for%20stoking%20Hindu%20hyper-nationalism%20again%2C%20to%20win%20yet%20another%20general%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWill%20the%20Union%20government%20be%20able%20to%20control%20the%20reaction%20in%20Kashmir%3F%20Modi%20would%20like%20us%20to%20believe%20that%20it%20will%2C%20because%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20people%20of%20the%20Valley%20will%20oppose%20the%20return%20of%20violence%2C%20and%20the%20loss%20of%20business%20and%20livelihoods%20that%20it%20will%20entail.%20That%20was%20what%20his%20government%E2%80%99s%20affidavit%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20been%20intended%20to%20impress%20upon%20it.%20But%20even%20a%20cursory%20look%20at%20the%20reality%20behind%20the%20virtual%20blackout%20of%20political%20news%20from%20the%20Valley%20shows%20that%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20affidavit%20is%20a%20tissue%20of%20falsehoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20it%2C%20the%20government%20has%20claimed%20that%20%E2%80%98the%20entire%20region%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20has%20witnessed%20an%20%E2%80%9Cunprecedented%E2%80%9D%20era%20of%20peace%2C%20progress%2C%20and%20prosperity%2C%20with%20street%20violence%20orchestrated%20by%20terrorists%20and%20secessionist%20networks%20becoming%20a%20thing%20of%20the%20past%E2%80%99.%20Modi%20may%20even%20have%20persuaded%20himself%20that%20this%20is%20actually%20true%20but%20data%20collected%20painstakingly%20by%20the%20South%20Asia%20Terrorism%20Portal%20(SATP)%20show%20that%20it%20is%20the%20opposite%20of%20the%20truth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20SATP%2C%20in%20the%20four%20years%20from%202019%20to%202022%2C%20there%20were%20729%20incidents%20involving%20the%20killing%20of%20civilians%2C%20militants%20and%20security%20forces%20%E2%80%93%20an%20average%20of%20one%20incident%20every%20two%20days!%20In%20these%2C%20the%20security%20forces%20killed%20781%20militants%20and%20suffered%20209%20deaths.%20Kashmir%20had%20therefore%20seen%20990%20deaths%20in%201%2C460%20days%2C%20i.e.%20one%20death%20caused%20by%20militancy-related%20violence%2C%20every%2036%20hours!%20Unless%20it%20is%20SATP%20that%20has%20been%20lying%2C%20these%20figures%20show%20that%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20has%20told%20a%20blatant%20lie%20in%20a%20sworn%20affidavit%20to%20the%20highest%20court%20of%20the%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHaving%20done%20so%2C%20it%20will%20have%20no%20option%20but%20to%20live%20out%20that%20lie.%20Since%20it%20can%20only%20do%20this%20by%20crushing%20the%20popular%20discontent%20in%20Kashmir%20as%20rapidly%20and%20completely%20as%20possible%2C%20this%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20level%20of%20repression%20that%20Kashmir%20has%20never%20experienced%20before.%20Furthermore%2C%20given%20the%20way%20in%20which%20Modi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdisturbing-similarities-in-modis-journey-from-godhra-2002-to-pulwama-2019%5C%22%3Eturned%20the%20Gujarat%20riots%20of%202002%20and%20the%20Pulwama%20suicide%20bombing%20of%202019%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20political%20advantage%2C%20it%20is%20a%20safe%20bet%20that%20he%20will%20try%20to%20do%20the%20same%20with%20the%20pogrom%20that%20will%20follow%20in%20Kashmir.%20And%2C%20given%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20spectacular%20rise%20after%20both%20those%20tragic%20events%2C%C2%A0%20there%20is%20every%20likelihood%20that%20he%20will%20succeed%20yet%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F02%2F19124016%2FModi-Pulwama.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F02%2F19124016%2FModi-Pulwama.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F02%2F19124016%2FModi-Pulwama-300x130.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F02%2F19124016%2FModi-Pulwama-1024x444.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-339017%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22520%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20paying%20tribute%20to%20the%20CRPF%20soldiers%20killed%20in%20the%20Pulwama%20attack.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAverting%20this%20design%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESo%20one%20of%20the%20first%20questions%20the%20opposition%20will%20need%20to%20discuss%2C%20when%20formulating%20a%20common%20programme%20of%20action%20to%20present%20to%20the%20people%20before%20the%20next%20election%2C%20is%20how%20to%20forestall%20an%20attempt%20by%20Modi%20to%20repeat%20his%20earlier%20successes%20by%20unleashing%20another%20reign%20of%20terror%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20and%20using%20the%20reaction%20that%20will%20evoke%20from%20the%20youth%20to%20inflame%20the%20dormant%20distrust%20of%20Muslims%20in%20Hindu%20hearts%20in%20the%20rest%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20starting%20point%20for%20frustrating%20this%20design%20is%20to%20understand%2C%20and%20accept%2C%20that%20Partition%2C%20and%20the%20slaughter%20of%20innocents%20that%20followed%2C%20severely%20damaged%20the%20syncretic%20Ganga-Yamuni%20culture%20built%20over%20the%20previous%20600%20years%20all%20over%20north%20India.%20In%20Pakistan%2C%20it%20led%20to%20a%20%E2%80%98purification%E2%80%99%20of%20Sunni%20Islam%2C%20exemplified%20by%20the%20teachings%20of%20Maulana%20Maududi%2C%20that%20led%20to%20the%20official%20excommunication%20of%20various%20Shia%20factions%2C%20most%20notably%20the%20Ahmadiyyas%2C%20and%20fostered%20the%20rise%20of%20violent%20extremist%20organisations%20like%20the%20Lashkar-e-Taiba%2C%20the%20Lashkar-e-Jhangvi%20and%20the%20Taliban%20%E2%80%93%20who%20offered%20to%20further%20%E2%80%98purify%E2%80%99%20Islam%20in%20Pakistan%2C%20in%20exchange%20for%20being%20allowed%20to%20%E2%80%98liberate%E2%80%99%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20India%2C%20Partition%2C%20and%20the%20subsequent%20conflict%20with%20Pakistan%2C%20hardened%C2%A0%20Hindu%20distrust%20of%20Muslims%20and%20discredited%20the%20syncretic%20Islam%20that%20had%20emerged%20out%20of%20centuries%20of%20peaceful%20co-existence%20and%20been%20codified%20by%20Akbar%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EDin-e-Elahi%3C%2Fem%3E.%20That%20is%20the%20syncretism%20that%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20gave%20his%20life%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20preserve.%20How%20deeply%20embedded%20it%20remains%20in%20the%20Indian%20Muslim%20psyche%2C%20even%2075%20years%20and%20three%20Indo-Pak%20wars%20after%20Partition%2C%20can%20be%20judged%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20there%20has%20not%20been%20a%20single%20Sunni-Shia%20communal%20riot%20of%20significance%20in%20India%20after%20independence%2C%20when%20this%20was%20an%20annual%20event%20in%20the%2019th%20and%20early%2020th%20centuries.%20By%20contrast%2C%20in%20Pakistan%2C%20the%20Lashkar-e-Jhangvi%20was%20given%20a%20relatively%20free%20reign%20to%20kill%20Shias%20in%20some%20parts%20of%20Pakistan%20such%20as%20Sindh%20and%20Baltistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThanks%20to%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20sacrifice%2C%20and%20the%20relentless%20efforts%20of%20Nehru%2C%20Maulana%20Azad%20and%20others%2C%20syncretism%20has%20remained%20strong%20in%20India.%20Out%20of%20more%20than%20200%20million%20Indian%20Muslims%2C%20only%2018%20joined%20al%20Qaeda%2C%20and%20less%20than%20100%20joined%20ISIS.%20Nearly%20all%20of%20these%2C%20moreover%2C%20were%20migrants%20working%20in%20the%20Gulf%2C%20who%20were%20lured%20into%20joining%20ISIS%20in%20part%20at%20least%20by%20the%20prospect%20of%20escaping%20from%20their%20miserable%20conditions%20of%20work%20in%20there.%20By%20contrast%2C%20more%20than%205%2C000%20Europeans%20joined%20it%2C%20among%20whom%20only%20a%20minority%20were%20children%20of%20immigrants%20from%20the%20middle%20east.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhat%20the%20post-partition%20conflict%20with%20Pakistan%20over%20Kashmir%20has%20erased%20from%20the%20Hindu%20mind%20is%20that%20this%20syncretism%20is%20not%20only%20strongest%20in%20Kashmir%20but%20has%20survived%20despite%20the%20outbreak%20of%20insurgency%20in%201989%20only%20because%20Article%20370%20prevented%20a%20large%20number%20of%20people%20from%20other%20parts%20of%20India%20from%20settling%20in%20Kashmir.%20Since%20the%20outbreak%2C%20first%20army%20and%20then%20police%20repression%20has%20driven%20more%20and%20more%20of%20the%20youth%20into%20the%20arms%20of%20the%20Jamaat-i-Islami%20and%20the%20Ahl-e-Hadis.%20But%20syncretic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fkiren-rijiju-nehru-blunders-kashmir-hindsight%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EReshi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20corruption%20of%20Rishi)%20Islam%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20survived%20in%20spite%20of%20this%20and%20remains%20the%20dominant%20form%20of%20Islam%20in%20Kashmir%20even%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EReshi%20Islam%20is%20full%20of%20practices%20incorporated%20into%20it%20from%20Hinduism.%20Among%20these%20is%20%3Cem%3EAuradh-e-Fidrat%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20morning%20prayer%20to%20the%20rising%20sun%20that%20has%20no%20equivalent%20in%20any%20branch%20of%20Islam%20outside%20Kashmir%2C%20because%20it%20is%20an%20incorporation%20of%20%3Cem%3ESurya%20Namaskar%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Another%20is%20the%20practice%20of%20invoking%20one%E2%80%99s%20ancestors%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20every%20major%20prayer%20or%20religious%20function%20%E2%80%93%20again%20normal%20in%20Hinduism%20but%20%3Cem%3Eharaam%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20Sunni%20Islam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EBut%20perhaps%20most%20telling%20is%20the%20nature%20of%20Kashmiri%20cuisine.%20Till%20today%2C%20there%20is%20not%20only%20no%20beef%20in%20it%20but%20also%20no%20chicken%20and%20no%20eggs.%20There%20is%20also%2C%20in%20my%20experience%2C%20no%20garlic.%20In%20short%2C%20Kashmiri%20cuisine%20is%2C%20till%20today%2C%20indistinguishable%20from%20the%20cuisine%20of%20Shaivite%20Brahmins%20%E2%80%93%20which%2C%20of%20course%2C%20was%20what%20Kashmiris%20were%20till%20the%20arrival%20of%20Sufi%20Islam%20from%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThese%20are%20only%20some%20of%20the%20more%20superficial%20differences%20between%20Reshi%20and%20Sunni%20Islam.%20Other%2C%20more%20profound%2C%20differences%20are%20the%20worship%20of%20relics%20of%20saints%2C%20and%20of%20the%20shrines%20where%20they%20are%20buried%2C%20that%20one%20finds%20in%20Reshi%2C%20and%20some%20other%20variants%20of%20Shia%20Islam%2C%20but%20is%20forbidden%20in%20Sunni%20Islam.%20These%20differences%20were%20noted%20by%20no%20less%20eminent%20a%20person%20than%20Mohammed%20Ali%20Jinnah%20in%201946%2C%20and%20led%20him%20to%20reject%20a%20request%20by%20the%20Jammu-based%20J%26amp%3BK%20Muslim%20Conference%20to%20allow%20it%20to%20join%20the%20Muslim%20League.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThese%20differences%20also%20explain%20why%2C%20despite%20almost%20a%20quarter%20of%20a%20million%20traumatised%20refugees%20from%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20Radcliffe%20line%20passing%20through%20Jammu%20in%201947%2C%20the%20entire%20princely%20state%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20and%20the%20Valley%20in%20particular%2C%20remained%20free%20from%20communal%20violence%20till%20almost%20the%20end%20of%20October%201947%2C%C2%A0%20while%20the%20rest%20of%20India%20burned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThat%20is%20the%20communal%20harmony%20that%20both%20Nehru%20and%20Sheikh%20Abdullah%20cherished%20and%20were%20determined%20to%20protect.%20Even%20the%20rigging%20of%20elections%2C%20that%20began%20in%20a%20small%20way%20as%20early%20as%201952%2C%20was%20not%20designed%20to%20prevent%20Kashmiri%20Muslims%20from%20expressing%20a%20desire%20to%20join%20Pakistan%20but%20to%20prevent%20Hindu%20zealots%2C%20concentrated%20in%20Jammu%2C%20from%20being%20able%20to%20drag%20Kashmir%20into%20the%20mire%20of%20Indian%20communal%20politics.%20This%20threat%20had%20arisen%20in%20November%201947%2C%20when%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Praja%20Parishad%20was%20created%20in%20Jammu%20by%C2%A0%20Balraj%20Madhok%2C%20a%20key%20member%20of%20the%20RSS%2C%20with%20the%20express%20purpose%20of%20opposing%20the%20special%20status%20granted%20to%20the%20state%20under%20Article%20370%20of%20the%20constitution.%20This%20brought%20the%20communal%20politics%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20India%20into%20the%20state%20and%20threatened%20to%20undo%20precisely%20what%20Nehru%2C%20Sheikh%20Abdullah%20and%20Maharaja%20Hari%20Singh%20had%20been%20trying%20their%20level%20best%2C%20in%20their%20own%20ways%2C%20to%20prevent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F08%2F13124425%2FImage-from-iOS.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F08%2F13124425%2FImage-from-iOS.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F08%2F13124425%2FImage-from-iOS-300x166.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F08%2F13124425%2FImage-from-iOS-1024x567.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-387846%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22665%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EJawaharlal%20Nehru%20and%20Sheikh%20Abdullah.%20Photo%3A%20Oxford%20University%20Press%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20rigging%20that%20began%20then%20was%20designed%20to%20insulate%20Kashmiriyat%20not%20from%20the%20pull%20of%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20Sunni%20Islam%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20but%20against%20the%20push%20of%20Hindu%20intolerance%2C%20later%20dignified%20as%20Hindutva%2C%20in%20Jammu.%20This%20made%20it%20necessary%20for%20the%20National%20Conference%20to%20ensure%20that%20it%20always%20won%20a%20sufficient%20number%20of%20seats%20to%20obtain%20a%20majority%20in%20the%20state%20legislature.%20Rigging%20up%20to%20half%20of%20the%20constituencies%20in%20Kashmir%20became%20the%20surest%20way%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20National%20Conference%20stayed%20in%20power%20at%20least%20until%20India%20won%20its%20case%20in%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%20and%20Pakistan%20withdrew%20from%20PoK.%20That%2C%20of%20course%2C%20never%20happened.%20So%2C%20particularly%20after%20the%20arrest%20of%20Sheikh%20Abdullah%2C%C2%A0%20what%20had%20begun%20as%20a%20temporary%20expedient%20became%20a%20routine%20feature%20of%20all%20elections%20in%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20casualty%20in%20this%20power%20game%20was%20democracy.%20For%20the%20continuous%20rigging%20of%20the%20elections%20in%20Kashmir%20to%20checkmate%20the%20rise%20of%20Hindutva%20in%20Jammu%20frustrated%20every%20attempt%20to%20create%20a%20democratic%20opposition%20in%20the%20Valley.%20That%20is%20what%20finally%20triggered%20the%20insurgency%20that%20began%20after%20the%20rigged%20elections%20of%201987%20and%20burst%20into%20flames%20in%20December%201989.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESo%20the%20first%20challenge%20that%20a%20combined%20opposition%20will%20have%20to%20face%20is%20to%20find%20a%20way%20to%20prevent%20Modi%20from%20turning%20a%20defeat%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20into%20a%20victory%20in%20the%202024%20elections.%20The%20way%20to%20do%20this%20is%20not%20by%20condemning%20the%20military%20crackdown%20that%20Modi%20is%20sure%20to%20impose%20on%20the%20state%20the%20moment%20he%20receives%20an%20adverse%20verdict%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20but%20to%20demand%20an%20immediate%20election%20in%20the%20whole%20of%20the%20pre-2019%20state%20to%20elect%20the%20members%20of%20a%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20that%20will%20be%20empowered%20to%20ratify%20the%20original%20or%20a%20modified%20Article%20370.%20This%20will%20be%20necessary%20because%20it%20was%20a%20Kashmiri%20Constituent%20Assembly%20that%20ratified%20Article%20370%20in%20November%201956.%20Since%20this%20assembly%20then%20dissolved%20itself%2C%20a%20new%20one%20will%20have%20to%20be%20created%20through%20an%20election%2C%20to%20ratify%20its%20reinstatement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EA%20formal%20commitment%20by%20the%20opposition%20to%20leave%20the%20choice%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20future%20to%20the%20Kashmiris%2C%20made%20immediately%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20decision%20if%20it%20rules%20against%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20special%20status%2C%20will%20prevent%20the%20resurgence%20of%20armed%20insurrection%20because%20the%20youth%20who%20favour%20this%20will%20receive%20no%20support%20from%20their%20elders.%20That%20was%20what%20had%20made%20the%20insurgency%20of%20the%2090s%20peter%20out.%20The%20prospect%20of%20being%20able%20to%20decide%20their%20own%20future%20democratically%20will%20have%20the%20same%20effect%20once%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EPrem%20Shankar%20Jha%20is%20a%20veteran%20journalist%20and%20author%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3EKashmir%201947%3A%20Rival%20Versions%20of%20History%3Cem%3E%20published%20by%20OUP%20in%201996.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689863445000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F15203328%2F2022_8img15_Aug_2022_PTI08_15_2022_000321B-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Findia-democracy-survival-complacency%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20immediate%20threat%20lies%20in%20Kashmir.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Findia-democracy-survival-complacency%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SRK%20to%20Akshay%3A%20AI%20used%20to%20reimagine%20actors%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689863400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-101989085%2Cimgsize-78970.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fweb-stories%2Fharrison-ford-shah-rukh-khan-akshay-kumar-ai-used-to-reimagine-actors%2Fphotostory%2F101989085.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F101989085.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3Eharrison%20ford%2C%20shah%20rukh%20khan%2C%20akshay%20kumar%3A%20ai%20used%20to%20reimagine%20actors%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Arjun%20Pereira%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fweb-stories%2Fharrison-ford-shah-rukh-khan-akshay-kumar-ai-used-to-reimagine-actors%2Fphotostory%2F101989085.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Play%2C%20Learn%2C%20Grow%2C%20Repeat%3A%20A%20Peak%20Inside%20India%E2%80%99s%20Innovative%2C%20DIY%2C%20Sustainable%20Playgrounds%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20published%20in%20collaboration%20with%20EkStep%20Foundation.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Pooja%20Rai%20was%20a%20student%20of%20architecture%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F275217%2Fiit-kharagpur-innovation-oral-cancer-screening-cheap-device%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndian%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20(IIT)%2C%20Kharagpur%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20would%20volunteer%20at%20Disha%20Seema%20Care%20Centre%2C%20a%20school%20for%20underprivileged%20children%20located%20on%20campus.%20During%20one%20visit%2C%20she%20observed%20a%20few%20girls%20playing%20on%20broken%20cement%20pipes%20while%20some%20construction%20work%20was%20going%20on%20nearby.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20extremely%20unsafe%20because%20you%20had%20wires%20coming%20out%20of%20the%20pipes%20and%20there%20were%20broken%20pieces%20of%20cement%20lying%20around.%20I%20also%20saw%20some%20boys%20at%20school%20trying%20to%20play%20a%20game%20of%20badminton%20with%20their%20slippers.%20Even%20though%20there%20was%20so%20much%20joy%20in%20that%20space%2C%20it%20just%20made%20me%20think%20that%20these%20children%20don%E2%80%99t%20even%20have%20access%20to%20something%20as%20simple%20as%20a%20playground.%20Talking%20to%20my%20friend%20that%20evening%2C%20we%20discussed%20how%20we%20could%20use%20all%20the%20design%20knowledge%20that%20we%20learned%20to%20build%20a%20playground%20for%20these%20kids%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Rai%2C%20speaking%20to%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20that%20Pooja%20and%20her%20batchmates%20were%20students%2C%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20money.%20Instead%20of%20building%20a%20conventional%20playground%20with%20a%20jungle%20gym%2C%20merry%20go%20round%20and%20slides%2C%20they%20got%20innovative%2C%20brought%20a%20few%20tires%20together%2C%20and%20built%20a%20different%20kind%20of%20playground.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201193px)%20100vw%2C%201193px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playgrounds-8-1689854320.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221193%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Playgrounds%20for%20children%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playgrounds-8-1689854320.jpg%201193w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playgrounds-8-1689854320-300x183.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playgrounds-8-1689854320-500x306.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playgrounds-8-1689854320-768x469.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playgrounds-8-1689854320-150x92.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-324513%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22729%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EPlayground%20at%20the%20Disha%20Seema%20Care%20Centre.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20%E2%80%98DIY%E2%80%99%20playground%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CInitially%2C%20we%20struggled%20to%20collect%20tires%2C%20but%20we%20got%20lucky%20after%20reaching%20out%20to%20a%20few%20companies.%20Michelin%2C%20a%20global%20tyre%20manufacturer%2C%20sponsored%20the%20very%20first%20playground%20we%20built.%20They%20sent%20us%20used%20tires%2C%20with%20which%20we%20built%20swings%20and%20other%20play%20elements%20for%20children.%20They%20also%20sponsored%20a%20part%20of%20the%20project%2C%20while%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20funding%20came%20from%20our%20college%20alumni.%20We%20built%20our%20first%20playground%20in%202015%20and%20it%20was%20completely%20DIY%20(%E2%80%98do%20it%20yourself%E2%80%99)%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20Rai%20and%20her%20batchmates%20built%20here%20was%20a%20low-cost%20(barely%20Rs%2020%2C000)%20and%20sustainable%20playground%20for%20underprivileged%20children.%20According%20to%20Rai%2C%20mass%20produced%20recreational%20equipment%20for%20building%20a%20playground%20at%20the%20time%20would%20typically%20cost%20about%20Rs%202%20lakh.%20What%20followed%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20media%20coverage%20and%20inquiries%20from%20all%20around%20the%20country%20to%20build%20similar%20structures.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFast%20forward%20to%20January%202017%2C%20Rai%20and%20her%20friends%20quit%20their%20jobs%20full%20time%20and%20established%20a%20Bengaluru-based%20non-profit%20called%20Anthill%20Creations%2C%20which%20%E2%80%9Ctransforms%20spaces%20into%20interactive%20and%20sustainable%20playgrounds%20by%20upcycling%20waste%20materials%20like%20tyres%2C%20oil%20and%20cable%20drums.%E2%80%9D%20So%20far%2C%20they%20have%20built%20around%20380%20low-cost%20and%20sustainable%20playgrounds%20for%20children%20across%2022%20states%20including%20Karnataka%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20Delhi%2C%20Odisha%2C%20Meghalaya%2C%20Tripura%2C%20amongst%20others.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20why%20are%20playgrounds%20important%20for%20children%20in%20the%20first%20place%3F%20Educationists%20note%20that%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcampaign.thebetterindia.com%2Fchildhooddialogues%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eearly%20childhood%20care%20and%20education%20(ECCE)%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20play-based%20learning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-captioned%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Ftv%2FCZjg3gapFqJ%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Ftv%2FCZjg3gapFqJ%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Ftv%2FCZjg3gapFqJ%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20post%20shared%20by%20Anthill%20Creations%20Foundation%20(%40anthillcreations)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhy%20play-based%20learning%20matters%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBased%20on%20science%20and%20what%20we%20know%2C%20and%20from%20a%20lot%20of%20experience%2C%20play%20is%20an%20important%20way%20for%20the%20child%20to%20learn.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20it%20is%20not%20just%20%E2%80%98playing%E2%80%99%20as%20we%20know%20it.%20It%20includes%20singing%20songs%2C%20conversations%2C%20stories%2C%20music%2C%20puzzles%2C%20dancing%2C%20etc.%20It%20is%20what%20the%20child%20does%20naturally%2C%20or%20as%20we%20say%2C%20%E2%80%98play%20is%20child%E2%80%99s%20work%E2%80%99.%20When%20a%20child%20is%20playing%2C%20they%20are%20learning%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Shankar%20Maruwada%2C%20CEO%20and%20co-founder%20of%20EkStep%20Foundation%20and%20member%2C%20National%20Steering%20Committee%20for%20the%20National%20Curriculum%20Frameworks%20(NCF)%2C%20in%20an%20earlier%20interaction%20with%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20line%20of%20thinking%20has%20been%20emphasised%20by%20policymakers%20in%20India%20with%20the%20New%20Education%20Policy%20(NEP)%202020%20and%20the%20National%20Curriculum%20Framework%20for%20School%20Education%20(NCF)%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(You%20can%20read%20more%20about%20play-based%20learning%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F298277%2Fnep-early-childhood-care-and-education-play-based-learning-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3Eand%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F304738%2Fnational-curriculum-framework-for-foundational-stage-education-children-india-ekstep%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20are%20different%20modes%20of%20play%2C%20a%20playground%20presents%20one%20of%20the%20key%20platforms%20where%20a%20child%20can%20engage%20in%20play-based%20learning%20for%20cognitive%20and%20behavioural%20development.%20But%20nearly%20half%20of%20all%20public-funded%20schools%20in%20India%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20playgrounds%2C%20notes%20government%20data.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fover-40-govt-schools-dont-have-power-playgrounds-parliamentary-panel%2Farticle61964470.ece%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUnified%20District%20Information%20System%20for%20Education%20(UDISE)%202017-18%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20less%20than%2057%25%20of%20schools%20have%20playgrounds.%20In%20states%20like%20Odisha%20and%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20less%20than%2030%25%20of%20schools%20have%20playgrounds.%20Other%20surveys%20indicate%20that%20even%20major%20cities%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20enough%20playgrounds.%20Take%20Bengaluru%2C%20for%20example.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Janaagraha%2C%20a%20Bengaluru-based%20think-tank%2C%20%E2%80%9CWith%20a%20population%20of%2012%20million%20(unofficial%20estimate%2C%208.4%20million%20as%20per%202011%20census)%20and%20an%20area%20of%20709%20sq.km%2C%20the%20city%20of%20Bengaluru%20has%20only%2019.31%20sq.km%20dedicated%20towards%20open%20spaces%20like%20parks%20and%20playgrounds.%20This%20translates%20to%202.2%20sq.m%20of%20open%20space%20per%20person%2C%20which%20is%20significantly%20short%20of%20the%20recommended%2010-12%20sq.m%20by%20the%20URDPFI%20(Urban%20and%20Regional%20Development%20Plans%20Formulation%20and%20Implementation*)%20guidelines%20set%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Urban%20Development%20(MoUD)%2C%20India.%E2%80%9D%20What%E2%80%99s%20worse%2C%20only%2039%25%20of%20playgrounds%20in%20the%20city%20have%20playing%20equipment%20and%20facilities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESrikanth%20Viswanathan%2C%20CEO%20at%20Janaagraha%20Centre%20for%20Citizenship%20and%20Democracy%2C%20notes%20that%20although%20the%20survey%20was%20taken%20in%202017%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthings%20haven%E2%80%99t%20changed%20much%20since%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20an%20unfortunate%20reality%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Right%20of%20Children%20to%20Free%20and%20Compulsory%20Education%20Act%2C%202009%20(RTE)%20legislated%20by%20Parliament%20mandates%20that%20all%20school-going%20children%20between%20the%20ages%20of%206%20and%2014%20should%20be%20guaranteed%20access%20to%20playgrounds.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20797px)%20100vw%2C%20797px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playground-1-1689854030.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22797%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Playgrounds%20in%20India%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playground-1-1689854030.jpg%20797w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playground-1-1689854030-300x288.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playground-1-1689854030-500x480.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playground-1-1689854030-768x737.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playground-1-1689854030-150x144.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-324512%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22765%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EAccessibility%20for%20all%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20does%20it%20take%20to%20build%20a%20playground%3F%20Speaking%20to%20The%20%3Cstrong%3EBetter%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20Rai%20begins%20with%20first%20principles.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20basic%20principle%20we%20follow%20is%20that%20where%20there%20is%20a%20need%20for%20a%20playground%20and%20people%20cannot%20afford%20it%2C%20we%20are%20happy%20to%20build%20these%20structures%20in%20those%20areas%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20we%20have%20seen%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years%20is%20that%20even%20if%20we%20build%20one%20or%20two%20playgrounds%20in%20the%20area%2C%20it%20motivates%20other%20people%20in%20the%20surrounding%20areas%20and%20creates%20awareness%20around%20the%20importance%20of%20play%20and%20how%20much%20good%20it%20can%20do.%20The%20playground%20is%20also%20usually%20shared%20by%20nearby%20communities%20or%20schools.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20limited%20to%20the%20one%20school%20where%20we%20built%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%20far%2C%20Anthill%20Creations%20has%20built%20playgrounds%20in%20major%20cities%20like%20Bengaluru%2C%20Delhi%20and%20Mumbai%20to%20the%20remote%20corners%20of%20states%20like%20Meghalaya%20and%20Tripura.%20Here%E2%80%99s%20an%20example%20of%20how%20they%20built%20playgrounds%20for%20four%20government%20schools%20in%20rural%20Meghalaya.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20Abhishek%20Gowda%2C%20the%20sub-divisional%20officer%20(civil)%20of%20Dadenggre%20%5Bsubdivision%5D%20in%20West%20Garo%20Hills%20district%2C%20Meghalaya%2C%20recalls%20the%20work%20Anthill%20did.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20January%202023%2C%20Anthill%20Creations%20approached%20me%20to%20facilitate%20the%20site%20selection%20process%20for%20these%20playgrounds%20under%20their%20project%20titled%20%E2%80%98Bring%20Back%20Play%20by%20Making%20it%20Accessible%20to%20All%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%20Their%20team%20visited%20around%2010%20rural%20schools%20in%20my%20sub-division%2C%20and%20finalised%20on%20four%20where%20they%20would%20build%20playgrounds.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20March%2C%20the%20Anthill%20team%20began%20building%20these%20playgrounds%20using%20old%20rubber%20tires%20and%20other%20scrap%20material.%20You%20had%20see-saws%2C%20elephant-shaped%20play%20elements%20and%20swings%20made%20of%20scrap%20rubber%20tires%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Gowda.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20constructing%20these%20playgrounds%2C%20the%20Anthill%20team%20conducted%20an%20extensive%20quality%20check%20process%20to%20ensure%20that%20these%20structures%20are%20safe%20for%20children%20to%20use.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COnce%20the%20quality%20check%20was%20done%2C%20they%20handed%20over%20the%20playgrounds%20to%20their%20respective%20schools%20and%20communities.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20April%2C%20these%20playgrounds%20were%20built%20and%20ready%20to%20use.%20Today%2C%20children%20are%20actually%20utilising%20these%20playgrounds%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20enthusiasm%20and%20happiness.%20These%20playgrounds%20have%20also%20transformed%20the%20environment%20in%20these%20schools%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGowda%20and%20his%20administration%E2%80%99s%20task%20in%20building%20these%20playgrounds%20was%20simple.%20They%20provided%20any%20administrative%20and%20logistical%20support%20the%20Anthill%20team%20needed.%20Funding%20for%20this%20project%20came%20from%20the%20National%20Payments%20Corporation%20of%20India%20(NPCI)%E2%80%99s%20CSR%20fund%20and%20all%20the%20work%20of%20actually%20selecting%20the%20sites%20and%20building%20these%20playgrounds%20was%20done%20by%20the%20Anthill%20team.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAlthough%20the%20main%20objective%20is%20to%20develop%20play-based%20learning%20infrastructure%20for%20early%20childhood%20development%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20improvements%20in%20school%20enrolment%20numbers%20and%20reduction%20in%20dropouts.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20these%20colourful%20playgrounds%2C%20the%20atmosphere%20in%20these%20schools%20feel%20a%20lot%20more%20welcoming%20to%20children%2C%E2%80%9D%20notes%20Gowda.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAround%2080%25%20of%20the%20playgrounds%20Anthill%20has%20built%20are%20in%20government%20schools%2C%20but%20they%20also%20build%20them%20in%20public%20places.%20%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99ve%20built%20a%20lot%20of%20public%20park%20playgrounds%20in%20Bengaluru%20like%20in%20Agara%20Lake%2C%20for%20example.%20We%20also%20partnered%20with%20another%20organisation%20called%20Recity%20to%20start%20building%20playgrounds%20in%20tourist%20hotspots%20Nainital%20and%20Darjeeling%20so%20that%20there%E2%80%99s%20more%20awareness%20around%20recycling.%20Those%20are%20places%20where%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20visit%2C%20so%20they%20generate%20a%20lot%20of%20waste%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Rai.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20it%E2%80%99s%20challenging%20for%20us%20to%20work%20in%20public%20spaces%20because%20you%E2%80%99d%20have%20to%20work%20with%20multiple%20authorities.%20It%E2%80%99s%20difficult%20to%20get%20permission%20from%20all%20stakeholders%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESchools%2C%20however%2C%20are%20where%20most%20children%20are%20present.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20typically%2C%20what%20I%20have%20seen%20in%20government%20schools%20is%20that%20they%20keep%20their%20playgrounds%20open%20to%20neighbouring%20children.%20So%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20really%20just%20the%20school%20children%20who%20are%20playing%20in%20those%20playgrounds%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Rai.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201274px)%20100vw%2C%201274px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playground-5-1689860816.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221274%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Playgrounds%20for%20young%20boys%20and%20girls%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playground-5-1689860816.jpg%201274w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playground-5-1689860816-300x199.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playground-5-1689860816-500x331.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playground-5-1689860816-768x508.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playground-5-1689860816-150x99.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-324637%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22843%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFrom%20elephants%20and%20horses%20to%20rockets%20on%20the%20playground%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Rai%20and%20her%20colleagues%20started%20building%20playgrounds%2C%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20build%20the%20typical%20elements%20that%20already%20exist%20like%20a%20jungle%20gym%2C%20see-saw%2C%20merry%20go%20round%2C%20etc.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20correct%20way%20to%20go%20about%20any%20design%20is%20asking%20the%20user%20what%20they%20want%20to%20do.%20In%20the%20early%20days%2C%20we%20would%20talk%20to%20the%20children.%20Some%20of%20the%20very%20first%20designs%20that%20we%20developed%20were%20thanks%20to%20children.%20We%20used%20to%20go%20to%20these%20schools%20in%20Bengaluru%2C%20conduct%20activities%20and%20play%20games%20with%20them.%20Children%20used%20to%20come%20up%20with%20amazing%20ideas.%20They%20would%20want%20a%20slide%20from%20their%20classroom%20to%20the%20playground%20or%20a%20water%20fountain%20coming%20out%20of%20a%20slide.%20We%20did%20not%20exactly%20translate%20what%20they%20said%20but%20we%20got%20a%20sense%20of%20what%20they%20wanted%20in%20a%20playground%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20play%20elements%20you%20see%20on%20playgrounds%20built%20by%20Anthill%20like%20octopus%2C%20elephants%20or%20horses%20came%20from%20children.%20Other%20children%20wanted%20a%20rocket%20in%20their%20playground.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20tried%20to%20incorporate%20some%20of%20those%20major%20structural%20designs%2C%20but%20also%20keep%20activities%20in%20mind%20when%20we%20were%20designing%20those%20final%20elements.%20It%20took%20a%20lot%20of%20iterations.%20Not%20all%20of%20our%20design%20elements%20became%20successful%20in%20the%20first%20go%2C%20but%20we%20seek%20to%20ensure%20a%20constant%20feedback%20loop%20that%20happened.%20We%20still%20engage%20in%20these%20processes%2C%20but%20today%20we%20have%20around%20100%20different%20designs%20in%20our%20design%20library%20although%20we%20still%20take%20requests%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Rai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20we%E2%80%99re%20operating%20at%20a%20much%20larger%20scale%20today%2C%20we%20have%20this%20written%20site%20survey%20form%20that%20either%20we%20fill%20when%20we%20visit%20a%20site%20or%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20local%20community%20or%20a%20teacher%20who%20fills%20it%20out%20for%20us.%20That%20basically%20captures%20what%20children%20need%20and%20if%20there%20is%20anything%20in%20specific%20that%20like%20that%20particular%20community%20or%20school%20wants%20to%20do%2C%20we%20look%20at%20our%20design%20library%20and%20see%20what%20fits%20well%20into%20this%20playground.%20We%20try%20to%20leave%20some%20space%20for%20designing%20new%20elements%20as%20well%20because%20we%20want%20to%20give%20some%20unique%20touch%20to%20most%20of%20our%20playgrounds%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20756px)%20100vw%2C%20756px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FPretend-play-elements-Elephant-1689861074.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22756%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Innovative%20playgrounds%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FPretend-play-elements-Elephant-1689861074.jpg%20756w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FPretend-play-elements-Elephant-1689861074-281x300.jpg%20281w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FPretend-play-elements-Elephant-1689861074-500x534.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FPretend-play-elements-Elephant-1689861074-150x160.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-324647%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22807%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EPretend%20Play%20Element%20in%20the%20shape%20of%20an%20elephant.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHow%20do%20they%20make%20these%20playgrounds%20inclusive%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20stated%20earlier%2C%20there%20are%20playgrounds%20with%20elements%20that%20didn%E2%80%99t%20come%20from%20their%20design%20library.%20After%20all%2C%20they%20have%20to%20cater%20to%20a%20variety%20of%20children%2C%20including%20those%20living%20with%20disabilities.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202021%2C%20they%20built%20a%20playground%20in%20collaboration%20with%20the%20Sankalp%20Learning%20Centre%20in%20Chennai%20for%20children%20with%20autism%20and%20intellectual%20disabilities.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20playground%20designed%20for%20autistic%20children%20in%20our%20library.%20For%20projects%20like%20these%2C%20we%20spent%20time%20with%20the%20children%2C%20understanding%20what%20works%20for%20them%2C%20what%20will%20help%20in%20their%20therapy%20and%20use%20tactile%20sensors%20in%20the%20playgrounds%20which%20might%20help%20them.%20In%20terms%20of%20design%2C%20we%20wanted%20to%20do%20something%20tactile.%20We%20wanted%20children%20to%20just%20feel%20different%20kinds%20of%20senses%20and%20build%20something%20that%20they%20can%20touch%20with%20their%20hands%20and%20also%20play%20with%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Rai.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20included%20a%20xylophone%20for%20sensory%20stimulation%2C%20parallel%20pay%20bars%20for%20wrist%20and%20finger%20movements%2C%20a%20seesaw%20to%20encourage%20balance%20and%20body%20coordination%2C%20and%20a%20low%20height%20climber%20to%20ensure%20muscular%20movement%20and%20safety%20for%20the%20children%20while%20at%20play%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERai%20admits%20that%20Anthill%E2%80%99s%20playgrounds%20aren%E2%80%99t%20completely%20inclusive%20yet%2C%20but%20they%20try%20to%20make%20them%20accessible.%20%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99re%20incorporating%20play%20elements%20used%20in%20playgrounds%20built%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F293875%2Fworlds-first-braille-literacy-award-winning-device-annie-innovation-for-blind-children%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evisually-impaired%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20all%20our%20playgrounds.%20For%20example%2C%20we%20have%20introduced%20sound%20elements%20like%20xylophone%20or%20bells%20in%20all%20our%20playgrounds.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20make%20playgrounds%20inclusive%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20833px)%20100vw%2C%20833px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-for-the-blind-india-1689861447.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Playgrounds%20for%20blind%20children%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22833%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-for-the-blind-india-1689861447.jpg%20833w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-for-the-blind-india-1689861447-300x297.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-for-the-blind-india-1689861447-500x496.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-for-the-blind-india-1689861447-150x149.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-for-the-blind-india-1689861447-768x762.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-for-the-blind-india-1689861447-96x96.jpg%2096w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-324649%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22826%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAnthill%20recently%20built%20a%20playground%20for%20the%20Calcutta%20Blind%20School.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBuilding%20%E2%80%98community%20champions%E2%80%99%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20Anthill%20has%20learnt%20over%20the%20years%20is%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20better%20to%20involve%20the%20community%20early%20in%20the%20process%20right%20from%20the%20site%20selection%20to%20what%20they%20are%20designing.%20When%20they%20involve%20the%20community%20from%20the%20beginning%2C%20they%20take%20greater%20ownership%20of%20the%20playgrounds.%20Typically%2C%20what%20Anthill%20does%20is%20build%20a%20playground%2C%20and%20hands%20it%20over%20to%20the%20community%20to%20take%20care%20of%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20how%20do%20they%20obtain%20community%20buy-in%20for%20these%20playgrounds%3F%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20we%20work%20in%20a%20new%20geography%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20always%20a%20local%20organisation%20or%20NGO%20who%20might%20have%20been%20working%20in%20these%20communities%20for%20years%20and%20already%20have%20that%20relationship%20built%20with%20them.%20When%20they%20bring%20us%20in%2C%20there%20is%20that%20sense%20of%20respect%20and%20trust%20already%20established%20when%20we%20go%20in.%20On%20our%20end%2C%20we%20also%20spend%20time%20with%20people%20explaining%20to%20them%20what%20structure%20is%20going%20to%20come%20up%20here%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Rai.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20maintain%20costs%2C%20Anthill%20largely%20procures%20materials%20locally%20and%20employs%20local%20labour.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGiven%20the%20elements%20that%20we%E2%80%99ve%20designed%20are%20simple%20and%20basic%20like%20tires%20and%20metal%20drums%2C%20and%20engage%20in%20recycling%20and%20upcycling%2C%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20make%20sense%20to%20transport%20things%20from%20Bengaluru%20to%20Tripura.%20We%20procure%20materials%20locally%20because%20it%20saves%20cost%2C%20available%20locally.%20Where%20it%20becomes%20challenging%20is%20to%20ensure%20the%20quality%20that%20we%20want%20in%20these%20elements%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20overcome%20these%20concerns%2C%20we%20have%20a%20set%20of%20vendors%20in%20Kolkata%2C%20Delhi%20and%20Bengaluru%2C%20and%20we%20transport%20these%20joineries%20from%20one%20central%20hub%20to%20wherever%20we%20are%20building%20playgrounds.%20Elements%20like%20tires%20and%20metal%2C%20we%20procure%20locally%20because%20those%20are%20like%20the%20bigger%20bulk%20of%20what%20we%20kind%20of%20use%20to%20design%20these%20playgrounds.%20Given%20we%20have%20now%20built%20playgrounds%20in%2022%20different%20states%2C%20we%20have%20identified%20vendors%20and%20all%20of%20these%20communities%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20as%20stated%20earlier%2C%C2%A0%20Anthill%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20take%20ownership%20of%20the%20playgrounds%20they%20build.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20just%20facilitators%20who%20are%20enabling%20the%20local%20community%20or%20the%20school%20to%20build%20a%20playground.%20We%20bring%20in%20funding%20with%20the%20help%20of%20a%20corporation%20and%20provide%20our%20expertise%20in%20how%20to%20construct%20the%20playground.%20But%20after%20those%20six%20days%20of%20intervention%2C%20our%20major%20role%20is%20complete%20in%20building%20the%20playground%20and%20we%20hand%20it%20over%20to%20the%20community%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhether%20this%20handover%20period%20is%20over%20one%20or%20three%20months%2C%20it%20varies%20based%20on%20where%20the%20playground%20is%20located.%20They%20often%20complete%20building%20the%20playground%20in%20six%20days.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COn%20the%20last%20day%2C%20we%20do%20a%20quality%20check%20with%20the%20corporate%20who%E2%80%99s%20funding%20the%20project%20and%20the%20local%20headmaster%2C%20and%20make%20sure%20that%20the%20playground%20we%E2%80%99ve%20constructed%20meets%20all%20the%20basic%20quality%20measures.%20And%20then%20we%20proceed%20towards%20our%20adoption%20plan.%20We%20identify%20one%20community%20champion.%20It%20could%20be%20anyone%20from%20a%20headmaster%20to%20a%20teacher%20or%20an%20alumni%20of%20that%20school%2C%20who%20was%20involved%20in%20building%20that%20playground%20and%20is%20happy%20to%20volunteer%20their%20time.%20We%20maintain%20correspondence%20with%20them.%20After%20one%20month%2C%20we%20contact%20them%20to%20do%20a%20basic%20check%20on%20how%20children%20are%20playing%20in%20these%20playgrounds.%20We%20have%20a%20questionnaire%20that%20they%20answer%20to%20help%20us%20assess%20the%20impact%20of%20this%20playground.%20We%20get%20both%20quantitative%20and%20qualitative%20feedback%20and%20whenever%20we%E2%80%99re%20building%20a%20new%20play%20element%2C%20we%20receive%20some%20extra%20feedback%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201300px)%20100vw%2C%201300px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playground-7-1689861524.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221300%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Innovative%20playgrounds%20in%20India%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playground-7-1689861524.jpg%201300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playground-7-1689861524-300x141.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playground-7-1689861524-500x235.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playground-7-1689861524-768x360.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playground-7-1689861524-150x70.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-324650%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22610%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EInnovative%20play%20spaces.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Our%20playgrounds%20are%20like%20IKEA%20blocks%E2%80%99%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20handing%20their%20playgrounds%20over%20to%20communities%2C%20once%20a%20year%20(or%20once%20in%20two%20years)%20Anthill%20organises%20a%20drive%20where%20their%20team%20travels%20and%20conducts%20checks%20to%20ascertain%20the%20state%20of%20our%20older%20playgrounds.%20Making%20matters%20easier%2C%20their%20playgrounds%20are%20low-maintenance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20our%20playgrounds%20are%20DIY%2C%20we%20do%20not%20refabricate%20(play%20elements%20like)%20a%20conventional%20merry%20go%20round.%20If%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20screw%20coming%20loose%2C%20you%20have%20to%20replace%20the%20merry%20go%20round%20entirely.%20Our%20playgrounds%20are%20like%20IKEA%20blocks.%20You%20can%20fix%20them%2C%20take%20them%20off%20when%20you%20want%20and%20put%20them%20in%20another%20place%20held%20together%20by%20nuts%20and%20bolts%2C%E2%80%9D%20claims%20Rai.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20facilitate%20play%20for%20young%20children%2C%20Anthill%20Creations%20has%20come%20up%20with%20a%20variety%20of%20innovations%20to%20facilitate%20greater%20inclusivity%20and%20work%20within%20the%20confines%20of%20different%20circumstances.%20For%20example%2C%20they%20came%20up%20with%20the%20concept%20of%20a%20Play%20Library.%20%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20we%20used%20smaller%20tires%20to%20create%20seating%20spaces%20in%20a%20more%20interesting%20way%20where%20the%20entire%20space%20felt%20very%20inviting%20for%20children%20to%20play.%20We%20had%20basically%20converted%20a%20library%20into%20a%20play%20area%2C%E2%80%9D%20recalls%20Rai.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20one%20of%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20favourite%20innovations%20in%20recent%20years%20is%20this%20concept%20called%20%E2%80%98Playground%20on%20Wheels%E2%80%99%20which%20Anthill%20has%20developed.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20this%20idea%20honestly%20came%20when%20we%20were%20going%20around%20finding%20spaces%20in%20Mumbai%20and%20Bengaluru%20on%20where%20we%20can%20build%20these%20playgrounds%20for%20schools%20that%20contained%20three%20or%20four%20storeys%20and%20nothing%20else%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201514px)%20100vw%2C%201514px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FPlaygrounds-Anthill-123-1689861675.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221514%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Building%20innovative%20playgrounds%20for%20children%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FPlaygrounds-Anthill-123-1689861675.jpg%201514w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FPlaygrounds-Anthill-123-1689861675-300x137.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FPlaygrounds-Anthill-123-1689861675-500x229.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FPlaygrounds-Anthill-123-1689861675-768x351.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FPlaygrounds-Anthill-123-1689861675-150x69.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-324654%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22692%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EBuilding%20innovative%20playgrounds%20for%20children.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Mumbai%2C%20she%20recalls%20a%20teacher%20telling%20her%20that%20her%20students%20really%20needed%20space%20to%20play.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSo%20we%20came%20up%20with%20this%20concept%20of%20Playground%20on%20Wheels%2C%20which%20is%20basically%20a%20truck%20converted%20into%20a%20playground.%20It%20can%20be%20shared%20amongst%20different%20neighbourhoods%20and%20it%20can%20go%20from%20one%20place%20to%20another.%20Once%20the%20truck%20playground%20arrives%20at%20a%20location%20and%20opens%20up%2C%20you%E2%80%99ll%20find%20climbers%2C%20sandbox%20and%20other%20tactile%20elements%20that%20allow%20children%20to%20play%20in%20groups.%20Whenever%20the%20truck%20arrives%2C%20it%20becomes%20play%20time%20for%20those%20children%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20bit%20like%20ice%20cream%20trucks%20coming%20around%2C%20but%20also%20signifying%20to%20children%20that%20this%20is%20their%20playtime.%20In%20the%20next%20couple%20of%20months%2C%20we%20will%20build%20our%20first%20prototype%20of%20that%20truck.%20We%20also%20won%20an%20award%20from%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20for%20designing%20this%20Playground%20on%20Wheels%20and%20hoping%20it%20will%20be%20implemented%20very%20soon%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20come%20across%20any%20innovative%20ideas%20or%20construction%20executed%20in%20playgrounds%20in%20your%20city%3F%20We%E2%80%99d%20love%20to%20hear%20all%20about%20it.%20Send%20pictures%20and%20information%20about%20the%20playground%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aeditorial%40thebetterindia.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeditorial%40thebetterindia.com%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0with%20the%20subject%20line%20%E2%80%9CChildhood%20Dialogues%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Edited%20by%20Divya%20Sethu%3B%20Images%20courtesy%20Anthill%20Creations)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689863290000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAnthill-Playgrounds-8-1689854320.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D324494%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Anthill%20Creations%2C%20which%20transforms%20%E2%80%9Cspaces%20into%20interactive%20and%20sustainable%20playgrounds%20by%20upcycling%20waste%20materials%20like%20tyres%2C%20oil%20and%20cable%20drums%E2%80%9D%20has%20built%20around%20380%20playgrounds%20for%20children%20across%2022%20states.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Rinchen%20Norbu%20Wangchuk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Annu%20hits%20out%20at%20Nitesh%20Tiwari's%20Ramayan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689862768000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-101992176%2Cimgsize-44402.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fannu-kapoor-asks-kaun-hai-nitesh-tiwari-as-he-lashes-out-at-the-filmmaker-over-film-on-ramayana%2Farticleshow%2F101992176.cms%22%2C%22