Cases%20Against%20Them%3A%20ADR%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F07132908%2FIn_par_img.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKolkata%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Nearly%2044%25%20of%20sitting%20MLAs%20across%20the%20country%20have%20criminal%20cases%20against%20them%2C%20while%2028%25%20have%20a%20history%20of%20serious%20criminal%20cases%20including%20murder%2C%20attempt%20to%20murder%2C%20crimes%20against%20women%2C%20a%20new%20report%20released%20by%20the%20Association%20of%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%20has%20revealed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20titled%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadrindia.org%2Fcontent%2Fanalysis-sitting-mlas-28-state-assemblies-and-2-union-territories-india-2023%5C%22%3EAnalysis%20of%20Sitting%20MLAs%20from%2028%20State%20Assemblies%20and%202%20Union%20territories%20of%20India%202023%E2%80%B2%3C%2Fa%3E%20analyses%204%2C001%20of%20the%20total%204%2C033%20MLAs%20across%2028%20state%20assemblies%20and%20two%20Union%20territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20analysis%20is%20based%20on%20the%20self-sworn%20affidavits%20of%20the%20current%20MLAs%2C%20filed%20prior%20to%20contesting%20their%20last%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20reveals%20that%20of%20the%204%2C001%20MLAs%20analysed%20across%20state%20assemblies%2C%201%2C777%20(44%25)%20have%20declared%20criminal%20cases%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20many%20as%201%2C136%2C%20or%2028%25%2C%20have%20declared%20%E2%80%9Cserious%20criminal%20cases%E2%80%9D%20against%20them.%20While%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%20does%20not%20define%20a%20%E2%80%98serious%E2%80%99%20criminal%20case%2C%20ADR%20considers%20alleged%20cases%20of%20crimes%20like%20murder%2C%20attempt%20to%20murder%2C%20kidnapping%2C%20crimes%20against%20women%2C%20etc.%20as%20such.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%2047%20MLAs%20have%20declared%20cases%20related%20to%20murder%20under%20Section%20302%20of%20the%20IPC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20many%20as%20181%20MLAs%20have%20declared%20cases%20of%20attempt%20to%20murder%20under%20Section%20307%20of%20the%20IPC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20114%20MLAs%20have%20declared%20cases%20related%20to%20crimes%20against%20women%2C%20of%20which%2014%20MLAs%20have%20declared%20cases%20related%20to%20rape%20under%20IPC%20section%20376.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22301%5C%22%3ETotal%20MLAs%20across%20assemblies%20and%C2%A0%20Union%20territories%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22301%5C%22%3E4%2C001%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22301%5C%22%3EMLAs%20with%20criminal%20cases%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22301%5C%22%3E1%2C777%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22301%5C%22%3EMLAs%20with%20serious%20criminal%20cases%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22301%5C%22%3E1%2C136%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22301%5C%22%3EMLAs%20with%20murder%20cases%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22301%5C%22%3E47%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22301%5C%22%3EMLAs%20with%20attempt%20to%20murder%20cases%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22301%5C%22%3E181%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22301%5C%22%3EMLAs%20with%20cases%20related%20to%20crimes%20against%20women%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22301%5C%22%3E114%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22301%5C%22%3EMLAs%20with%20cases%20related%20to%20rape%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22301%5C%22%3E14%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKerala%20leads%20the%20states%20with%20the%20highest%20percentage%20of%20MLAs%20with%20criminal%20cases%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKerala%20leads%20the%20list%20with%2095%20of%20its%20135%20MLAs%20(75%25)%20having%20criminal%20cases%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20followed%20by%20Bihar%20with%20161%20of%20its%20242%20MLAs%20(67%25)%20having%20criminal%20cases%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelhi%2C%20with%2044%20of%20its%2070%20MLAs%20(63%25)%2C%20having%20criminal%20cases%20against%20them%2C%20follows%20the%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20list%20is%20further%20followed%20by%20Maharashtra%20with%20175%20of%20284%20MLAs%20(62%25)%3B%20Telangana%20with%2072%20of%20its%20118%20MLAs%20(61%25)%3B%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%20with%20134%20of%20224%20MLAs%20(60%25)%20having%20criminal%20cases%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDelhi%20tops%20the%20list%20for%20highest%20percentage%20of%20MLAs%20with%20serious%20criminal%20cases%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20many%20as%2037%20(53%25)%20out%20of%2070%20MLAs%20from%20Delhi%20have%20serious%20criminal%20cases%20against%20them%2C%20followed%20by%20Bihar%20with%20122%20(50%25)%20out%20of%20242%20MLAs%20having%20such%20cases%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20list%20continue%20with%20Maharashtra%20with%20114%20out%20of%20284%20MLAs%20(40%25)%2C%20Jharkhand%2031%20out%20of%2079%20MLAs%20(39%25)%2C%20Telangana%2046%20out%20of%20118%20MLAs%20(39%25)%20and%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20with%20155%20out%20of%20403%20MLAs%20(38%25)%20having%20declared%20serious%20criminal%20cases%20against%20themselves%20in%20their%20self-sworn%20affidavits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EParty-wise%20analysis%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20party-wise%20analysis%20of%20these%20MLAs%20has%20found%20that%2046%25%20of%20the%20Congress%20MLAs%20have%20criminal%20cases%20while%2027%25%20have%20serious%20criminal%20cases%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20has%20been%20found%20to%20fare%20slightly%20better%20as%2035%25%20of%20its%20MLAs%20have%20criminal%20cases%20while%2025%25%20have%20serious%20criminal%20cases%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20found%20all%20MLAs%20belonging%20to%2014%20parties%20had%20criminal%20cases%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20parties%20include%20Swabhimani%20Paksha%2C%20Revolutionary%20Marxist%20Party%20of%20India%2C%20Rashtriya%20Samaj%20Paksha%2C%20Maharashtra%20Navnirman%20Sena%2C%20Kerala%20Congress%20(Jacob)%2C%20Kalyana%20Rajya%20Pragathi%20Paksha%2C%20Janadhipathya%20Kerala%20Congress%2C%20Indian%20National%20Lok%20Dal%2C%20Haryana%20Lokhit%20Party%2C%20Goa%20Forward%20Party%2C%20Congress%20(Secular)%2C%20Prahar%20Janshakti%20Party%2C%20Kerala%20Congress%2C%20Jansatta%20Dal%20(Loktantrik).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20list%20is%20followed%20by%20All%20India%20Majlis-e-Ittehadul%20Muslimeen%20with%2090%25%20of%20its%20MLAs%20having%20criminal%20cases%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Union%20Muslim%20League%20has%2086%25%20of%20its%20MLAs%20with%20criminal%20cases%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist%E2%80%93Leninist)%20Liberation%20(85%25)%2C%20Rashtriya%20Lok%20Dal%20and%20Pattali%20Makkal%20Katchi%20(80%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20the%20larger%20regional%20parties%2C%20the%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20has%2076%25%20of%20its%20MLAs%20with%20criminal%20cases%2C%20follwoed%20by%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20(74%25)%2C%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%20(70%25)%2C%20Samajwadi%20Party%20(64%25)%2C%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(58%25)%2C%20YSR%20Congress%20Party%20(57%25)%2C%20Telangana%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(now%20known%20as%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20)%20(54%25)%2C%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%2052%25%2C%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%2043%25%2C%20and%20Trinamool%20Congress%20(42%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20number%20of%20crorepati%20MLAs%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20analyses%20the%20financial%20background%20of%20all%204%2C001%20MLAs%20across%20state%20assemblies%20and%20Union%20territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20many%20as%2088%20MLAs%2C%20or%202%25%2C%20of%20the%204%2C001%20politicians%20are%20billionaires%2C%20according%20