0Ronald%20Ross%20was%20awarded%20the%20Nobel%20Prize%20in%20Physiology%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20his%20work%20on%20malaria%2C%20by%20which%20he%20has%20shown%20how%20it%20enters%20the%20organism%20and%20thereby%20has%20laid%20the%20foundation%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F320276%2Fassam-woman-builds-community-centre-for-education-empowering-tribal-communities%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuccessful%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20this%20disease%20and%20methods%20of%20combating%20it%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20the%20scientific%20community%20cheered%20the%20efforts%20of%20Ross%2C%20one%20man%20remained%20forgotten.%20Bandyopadhyay%E2%80%99s%20hard%20work%20remained%20unrecognised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201390px)%20100vw%2C%201390px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FD4-Ss-iUEAEnKt1_11zon-1689682155.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221390%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ronald%20Ross%2C%20a%20British%20medical%20doctor%20who%20was%20awarded%20the%20Nobel%20Prize%20in%20Physiology%20for%20his%20discovery%20of%20the%20role%20of%20mosquitoes%20in%20malaria%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FD4-Ss-iUEAEnKt1_11zon-1689682155.jpg%201390w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FD4-Ss-iUEAEnKt1_11zon-1689682155-219x300.jpg%20219w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FD4-Ss-iUEAEnKt1_11zon-1689682155-500x686.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FD4-Ss-iUEAEnKt1_11zon-1689682155-768x1054.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FD4-Ss-iUEAEnKt1_11zon-1689682155-1119x1536.jpg%201119w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FD4-Ss-iUEAEnKt1_11zon-1689682155-150x206.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-324198%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221908%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ERonald%20Ross%2C%20a%20British%20medical%20doctor%20who%20was%20awarded%20the%20Nobel%20Prize%20in%20Physiology%20for%20his%20discovery%20of%20the%20role%20of%20mosquitoes%20in%20malaria%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Twitter%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FHeritageTimesIN%2Fstatus%2F1121277321040683010%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHeritage%20Times%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20did%20not%20sit%20well%20with%20many%20notable%20names%20of%20the%20time%2C%20who%20went%20on%20to%20raise%20their%20concerns%20about%20this.%20Among%20them%20were%20Indian%20physician%20Upendranath%20Brahmachari%2C%20writer%20and%20polymath%20Acharya%20Jagadish%20Chandra%20Bose%2C%20philosopher%20Brajendra%20Nath%20Seal%2C%20social%20reformer%20Sivanath%20Sastri%2C%20political%20figure%20Surendranath%20Banerjee%2C%20and%20historian%20Acharya%20Prafulla%20Chandra%20Ray.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20requested%20the%20then%20Viceroy%20of%20India%20Lord%20Curzon%20that%20Bandyopadhyay%20be%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F28236%2Findian-scientist-discovery-in-ending-malaria%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eawarded%20for%20his%20efforts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20Viceroy%20obliged.%20In%201903%2C%20Bandyopadhyay%20was%20awarded%20King%20Edward%20VII%E2%80%99s%20Gold%20Medal%20and%20felicitated%20at%20the%20University%20Senate%20Hall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201918%2C%20when%20a%20malaria%20epidemic%20struck%20the%20country%2C%20Dr%20Gopal%20Chandra%20Chattopadhyay%20started%20a%20public%20health%20movement%20to%20control%20the%20spread%2C%20and%20Bandyopadhyay%20joined%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20began%20educating%20the%20villagers%